title: 15 minute chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium high heat.
Add chicken.
Cook 5 minutes on each side.
Remove from skillet.
Add soup and water to skillet.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice and broccoli.
Top with chicken.
Cover.
Cook on low heat 5 minutes. Stir.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Peel and slice lengthwise carrots.
Cook in minimum amount of water until just tender.
Do not overcook!
Drain and put into a buttered casserole.
Mix together the remaining items and pour over carrots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle top with paprika and garnish with fresh parsley before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Mix cooked spaghetti, beaten eggs and Parmesan cheese (bottom layer).
Place a layer of Velvetta cheese on top.
Mix together cooked hamburger and spaghetti sauce.
Pour onto bottom layer. Cover with Mozzarella or Velveeta cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: crispix mix
directions: Heat dark Karo, brown sugar and margarine, but do not boil. Pour syrup mixture over cereal and walnuts.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Can substitute peanuts, almonds, etc. for walnuts.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in oblong buttered dish. Sprinkle crushed cracker crumbs over top and drizzle 3 tablespoons melted oleo over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Use as much chicken, onion and pepper as you want.
Mix all, simmer and serve over rice.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with noodles.

title: dill dip(for raw fresh vegetables)
directions: Serve with raw vegetables and chips.

title: danish stollen
directions: Put water and oleo in saucepan.
Let come to rolling boil and foaming.
Add vanilla.
Remove from stove and add flour.
Put in eggs, one at a time.
Stir well.
Put this mixture on top of strips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: judy's cheese cake
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping; blend well.
Spoon into crust.
Top with strawberries.
Chill until set.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat well in mixer.
Chill 1 hour.
Form a small ball.
Press down with a glass.
Dip in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine shortening and sugar; mix well.
Blend in eggs; add milk and vanilla.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Add pecans, dates and cherries; mix well.
Shape into balls using 1 tablespoon dough for 1 cookie.
Roll each ball of dough in cornflakes.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Top each cookie with 1/4 cherry.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not stack or store until cold.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, egg and dates in electric skillet at 300° about 6 minutes until color of dates change, then add Rice Krispies.
Cool slightly.
Make into balls while warm and roll in coconut or make into 1-inch ball and roll in powdered sugar and slice.

title: mary's nut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in order given.
When all is moistened, make a ball.
Place on a lightly floured surface.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick; cut with cookie cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° no longer than 10 minutes (don't let brown).

title: pull apart cinnamon rolls #1
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Put in rolls.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over rolls.
Cover tightly with foil and towel.
Let rise at room temperature or overnight in oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry popsicles
directions: Blend fruits until smooth.
Combine with juice, stirring well. Pour into eight 5-ounce paper cups.
Partially freeze.
Add popsicle sticks and freeze until firm.
Yields 8 servings.

title: my mothers 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Beat egg and butter together.
Sift flour and sugar together. Add to butter and egg mixture with milk.
Makes 3 (8-inch) cake layers or 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, spices and soda.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy. Add dry ingredients alternately with soup, mixing until smooth after each addition.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove and cool thoroughly on rack. Frost with cream cheese frosting or your favorite white frosting. Yields 16 servings.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Boil 6 to 7 minutes.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1 small onion (chopped).
Pour 1/2 stick butter over and mix.
Sprinkle with Colby cheese.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If not ready to eat, cover with foil and keep at 200°.
Serves 8.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients and shake with chicken parts. Melt the margarine in a shallow pan.
Lay chicken, skin side down and cook in oven 1/2 hour at 425°.
Turn and cook 15 minutes to 1/2 hour longer.

title: favorite stack cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to cream mixture just until blended.

title: key lime pie
directions: Soften gelatin in
cold
water.
Beat egg yolks.
Add 1 cup sugar, lime juice and salt.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly until
thickened.
Add
grated
peel
and
gelatin; stir until gelatin	is dissolved.
Tint pale green with coloring; cool.
Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.	Add remaining sugar slowly,
beating
after
each
addition.
Fold into lime mixture. Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Chill until firm.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice the apples into a baking dish. Add sugar to taste and the water.
Mix together.
Combine the 1/2 to 3/4 cup sugar, flour, butter and nuts (if desired) and pour this crumbly mixture over the apples. Bake slowly for at least 1 hour at 300°.
Serve hot or cold with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: air pudding(or diet mousse)
directions: Add the boiling water to the Jell-O.
Set aside to cool.
Whip the very cold evaporated milk and lemon juice until firm.
Slowly add the Jell-O mixture to the milk, continuing to whip.
When well mixed, place in dish and set in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: pesto with beans and rice
directions: Saute onion in skillet, sprayed with cooking spray, until the onion is browned. Add rice, tomatoes, pesto sauce and beans. Cook until heated. Serves 4.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: super scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in greased 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish. Make a white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and seasonings. Add cheese and onions; stir until cheese is melted.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: walnut bourbon balls
directions: Chop walnuts fine.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 40 balls.
Best if stored for several days before using.

title: tuna casserole(serves 1)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in baking dish and bake for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant and onion; drain off water.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese; mix well.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: bruce's beef barbecue
directions: Cook chuck roast in crock-pot until you can shred the beef. Add the rest of the ingredients and continue cooking in crock-pot for several hours.

title: lime slush
directions: Mix together in an ice cream pail and freeze.
To serve, fill glass 3/4 full with slush and add 7-Up to fill.

title: tuna ring
directions: Well-grease ring pan or a loaf pan.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: payday bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Heat until chips are melted.
Add Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Pour over marshmallow mixture and pat down.
Cool before cutting.
Easier to cut at room temperature.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla good. Bake pie crust and let cool.
Pour the mixture into crust.
Mix and add together cherry pie filling and almond flavoring.
Whip the whipping cream and fold into cherry pie mixture.
Pour over cream cheese mixture and refrigerate.

title: soft enchiladas casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion; season with salt and pepper.
Add taco sauce.
Heat chicken soup and milk.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Tear 4 soft tortillas into bite size pieces and cover bottom of casserole.
Add 1/2 of meat, 1/2 of soup and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pizza on english muffins
directions: Mix all together and put on muffin halves. Lay on cookie sheets and freeze, then return to muffin bags. Store in freezer. When ready to use, take out as many as you want and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°. If using without freezing, bake 10 minutes. Can use half of recipe for smaller amount.

title: aunt flossie's hot pepper relish
directions: Chop all ingredients.
Place in large enamel pot.
Add sugar, then pour vinegar over all.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Turn off heat.
Have jars hot.
Fill and seal. Makes 13 pints.

title: chicken artichoke
directions: Drain and cut up artichoke hearts; saute.
Saute chicken and garlic in olive oil over medium-high heat for about 5 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add to chicken when cooked.
Let thicken.
Add artichoke hearts and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over angel hair pasta or rice.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Wash, clean and scoop out inside of peppers. Drop in boiling water for approximately 5 to 10 minutes; drain.
Stuff peppers with mixture of remainder of ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or wrap in tin foil, freeze and heat frozen peppers for a longer period of time.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger, add next 4 ingredients and simmer 15 minutes. In large bowl, add all remaining ingredients.
Add hamburger mixture; mix together.
Serve immediately.

title: golden peach pie
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 1/3 cup syrup.
Combine sugar, flour, nutmeg and salt.
Add reserved syrup.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add butter, lemon juice, orange peel, almond extract and peaches.
Pour into prepared pie shell and arrange a lattice top.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Add egg yolks, then pineapple.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture. Use 1 crust for bottom; pour in pie mixture and put on top crust. Bake at 375° until crust browns.

title: apricot ham steak
directions: Trim fat around ham slice.
Place ham in a shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with sugar and stud sides with cloves.
Drain apricot juice.
Pour 1/3 cup of juice over ham.
Bake at 325° for one hour, basting often with juice in pan.
Arrange drained apricots on top; bake 15 minutes longer or until richly glazed.
Yield:
6 servings.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add taco mix seasoning.
Place 4 tortillas on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer hamburger, refried beans and tortillas.
Mix soups together and pour over the top. Put cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour until soups bubble. Bake at 350°.
Serve and garnish with taco chips, lettuce, tomatoes or sour cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, cinnamon, sugar and zucchini. Mix in dry ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° to 350° in greased floured pans (2 loaf pans).

title: pam's aunt ruby's rolls
directions: Mix salt, Crisco and sugar together.
Pour boiling water over mixture and stir until dissolved.
Mix yeast in cold water and add to first mixture.
Add eggs and flour.
Refrigerate (up to 4 days).

title: skillet beef italiano
directions: Brown beef in skillet, leaving meat in large chunks.
Add spaghetti sauce, water and oregano.
Add vegetables.
Bring to a full boil.
Separate vegetables and stir until blended.
Simmer 3 minutes.

title: fay nielsen's potato casserole
directions: Mix and top with Cheddar cheese.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and corn in a large bowl; stir well. Combine milk and remaining ingredients; stirring well.
Add to corn mixture.
Pour corn mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring twice during first 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vanilla rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into dessert dishes or serving bowls.
Place plastic wrap or wax paper on surface of hot pudding.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Serve sprinkled with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: crusty (soft center) spoon bread
directions: Combine and sift flour, corn meal, sugar and salt.
Add egg and 1 cup milk.
Blend batter well.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour in batter.
Pour generous 1/2 cup milk over top.
Bake in 375° oven about 45 minutes.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Make the night before.
Butter pan and add bread cubes.
Put cut-up sausage and cheese on bread and stir.
Beat eggs with milk and salt; pour over bread mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (or longer, depending on oven).

title: parmesan twists
directions: In an electric mixer (Cuisinart) beat butter, cream cheese and salt until smooth.
Work in flour with fingers or fork.
Flatten dough in tinfoil to form an 8 x 6-inch rectangle and chill overnight.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: In a medium saucepan combine sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from burner.
Add vanilla, peanut butter, cream and oats.
Drop on wax paper by the tablespoonful.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Ready to eat.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: creme de menthe cakes
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs, chocolate syrup, vanilla, salt and flour with hand mixer.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Store in an airtight container.
For an average size cup of tea, add 2 heaping teaspoonfuls of the spiced tea mix to hot water.

title: boursin cheese ball
directions: In medium sized bowl, mix cream cheese with herbs until well blended and smooth.
Refrigerate 30 minutes until firm.
Sprinkle lemon and pepper salt on sheet of wax paper.
Use hands to pat cheese into round flat shape.
Roll cheese in pepper until well covered.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 2 cups.

title: jello salad
directions: Make jello per package directions.
Chill until soft set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Refrigerate until firmly set.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Shape into balls. Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Yields 50 balls.

title: spinach and bacon soup
directions: Fry bacon; remove from pan.
Add onions; saute.
Sprinkle with flour and nutmeg.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk, potato flakes and chicken broth.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add bacon, cheese and spinach. Cook until cheese melts.

title: fettucine riccardo
directions: Heat butter, garlic and pepper in large skillet; add chicken, zucchini and half the seasoning salt and sear all sides of raw chicken.
Add pasta and remaining seasoning salt.
Add whipping cream and sour cream; blend well.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes to reduce creams to thick sauce.
Add cheese and blend well.
Makes 2 servings.

title: crunchy bars
directions: Press rolls in pan,
filling in holes; come up 1/2-inch on sides.
Pour Eagle Brand
milk
on
top.
Sprinkle with dry frosting mix.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: grape salad
directions: Cut cauliflower in small pieces.
Mix together with grapes and nuts.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and mustard and add to other ingredients.
Toss and enjoy.

title: dixie french salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Mix stuffing mixes and sage.
Add broth and mix lightly.
Stir in onions, celery and chicken.
Add more broth if too dry.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until it is lightly browned.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add rest of ingredients in order given, except cheese.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Spoon into greased baking dish, top with cheese and bake until cheese is melted.
Garnish with olives.

title: five pounds of fudge
directions: Combine chocolate chips, margarine and marshmallow; set aside. In heavy 4-quart saucepan, bring to a boil evaporated milk and sugar, stirring constantly.
When mixture reaches full rolling boil, cook for 8 minutes.
Pour over chocolate mixture in large bowl and stir until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: fruit ball
directions: Chop fruit and mix with cheese and pudding. Form a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and serve on graham crackers.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook all ingredients in crock-pot on low for 8 hours.

title: oatmeal icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt and add to creamed mixture. Mix in oatmeal, nuts and coconut.
Shape in rolls and refrigerate a couple of hours.
Slice and bake at 375° for 10 minutes on lightly greased cookie sheets.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add cream and Karo.
Boil to soft ball stage, remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until candy clings on side of boiler.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful on buttered dish.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs slightly, then stir in sugar, corn syrup, melted margarine and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until filling is slightly firm.

title: banana bread mayfair
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
In another bowl, combine bananas, sugar, eggs and butter.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture alternately with milk to banana mixture.
Add pecans and morsels.
Blend well.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Sprinkle top with chopped pecans (optional). Bake 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in Jell-O mold that has been sprayed with Pam.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix thoroughly.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients to cream mixture, blending well.
Fold in coconut, pecans and zucchini.
Spread on cookie sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed veal pocket
directions: Chop fine, parsley and onion.
In a large bowl, mix parsley, onion, spinach, bread crumbs, cheese, eggs, salt, pepper and garlic powder.

title: country clabber biscuits
directions: Grease three 9-inch aluminum pie pans and set aside.
Preheat oven to 425°.

title: southern sweet potato pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease bottom only of 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and spices in a large mixing bowl.
With a spoon, stir in sugar, eggs, oil and milk.
Stir to blend.
Mix in sweet potatoes, pecans and raisins. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
For easier slicing, wrap loaf and store overnight in a cool place.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine water, soup and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix food coloring with cocoa.
Set aside.
Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs.
Add food coloring and cocoa mixture. Rinse cocoa bowl out with buttermilk and vinegar.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add vanilla.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked shell and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
It will be slightly wiggly in the middle but will firm up as it cools.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: favorite cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll the dough on floured surface into a rectangle.
Brush dough with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture. Roll up like a jelly roll. Cut into 1-inch slices.
Place in greased muffin cups and brush tops with melted butter. Cover and let rise 20 minutes. Bake at 425° for about 18 to 20 minutes. Makes 1 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: aunt oval's hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a rolling boil that can't be stirred down; remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add Certo; mix and pour into jars.
Makes about 7 1/2 pints.

title: custard filled cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan with butter flavor Crisco.
Put greased pan in oven and let it get hot while you mix the batter.
Melt Crisco; mix with eggs until well blended. Add sugar, salt, milk and vinegar and beat well.
Mix in flour, cornmeal, baking powder and soda; mix just until the batter is smooth and no lumps appear.
Pour batter into heated dish.
Pour cream into center of batter; do not stir.
Bake for 1 hour or until lightly brown.

title: holiday dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Stir in dried beef, onion, green pepper and pepper; mix well.
Stir in sour cream.
Spoon into 8-inch pie plate or small, shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers or small bread slices.

title: holiday prune butter bread
directions: For prune butter, in a saucepan, combine prunes, lemon juice and 3/4 cup of water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 40 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in honey.
Cool. Place in a food processor bowl.
Process until smooth.
Cover and cool.

title: baked mexican steak
directions: Cut steak into 1/2-inch thickness.
Pound into meat 1/2 to 1 cup flour.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in bacon drippings; fry enough to brown it well on both sides.
Add tomatoes, onion and green pepper.
Cover.
Place in oven and bake at 300°.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine macaroni with all other ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Melt 5 tablespoons butter and soak in bread crumbs.
Place bread crumbs on top of casserole. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: debbie's taco dip
directions: Mix salad dressing and cream cheese until smooth.
Add all other ingredients and chill until blended.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid.
Combine reserved liquid with 57 sauce and honey.
Season chicken and place in baking dish.
Pour on sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.
Arrange pineapple slices on top during last 5 to 10 minutes.

title: "easy" barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer until onion is done.
Good for grilling, baking, etc.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Place potatoes and carrots in bottom of crock-pot.
In bowl, mix flour, salt and pepper. Coat meat with flour mixture. Place meat on top of vegetables in crock-pot. Add remaining ingredients to crock-pot.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour in a covered dish.
Serve with rye crackers.

title: big red ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add
sugar,
flour
and ice cream mix. Gradually add canned milk.	Mix
well.
Add Big Red soda water to fill 1 gallon freezer.

title: chocolate fluff pie
directions: Prepare pudding according to packaged directions and chill. Mix the cream cheese with 1/2 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread mixture in the bottom of the pie shell.
Once pudding is chilled, mix pudding with 2 to 3 cups of Cool Whip.
Blend until the consistency is light to medium brown in color.
Pour the pudding mixture over the cream cheese.
Top the pie with a generous amount of Cool Whip. For optional garnish, grate a Skor chocolate bar over the top of the Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: scripture cake
directions: Bake ingredients at 375° in loaf type pan until done.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark, add peanut butter, Rice Krispies, roasted peanuts and chow mein noodles; mix well.
Add marshmallows; stir. Drop on waxed paper with teaspoon.
Let cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix and cook cornstarch, sugar and water until mixture thickens and becomes clear.
Add 1 small box strawberry Jell-O powder.
Let cool.
After mixture cools, add 1 quart strawberries, drained.
Pour into pie shell before serving; add Cool Whip or whipped topping.
Garnish with strawberries (optional).

title: dee's cherry delight
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and margarine; press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.

title: six bean casserole
directions: Drain liquid from green, wax and lima beans.
Put in big casserole dish.
Add pinto beans, pork and beans and kidney beans. Add brown sugar, tomato sauce, mustard, onion, celery and browned hot sausage.
Cook in 350° oven for 2 hours.
Cook uncovered.

title: vegetable rotini
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, gradually stir soup into cream cheese. Add milk, mustard and pepper.
Over low heat, heat thoroughly, stirring often.
Add macaroni, vegetables and Parmesan cheese. Heat through, stirring often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine undrained pork and beans, bean salad, pineapple, barbecue sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven about 1 hour or until heated through.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl beat egg yolks; stir in sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice, rind and food coloring if desired.
Pour into prepared crust; bake for 8 minutes.
Cool. Chill.
Spread with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix and freeze. Set out early to start thawing (appx. 2-3 hours). Place in punch bowl and add 2-4 qts. ginger ale or 7-up.

title: desperation soup(for those days you can't think of anything to fix!)
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add Minute rice. Cover and let stand 5 minutes.

title: leg of lamb with mustard herb coating
directions: The night before combine all of the coating ingredients except the oil, then gradually beat in oil to make a mayonnaise-like consistency.
Paint this coating on the lamb with a spatula, then cover and refrigerate.
Bring out 30 minutes ahead the next day, then roast at 350° for about 1 hour or until it registers about 140° (about 10 minutes per pound for medium-rare, bone-in).
Let rest before carving.
May use a boned leg of lamb and grill instead.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook the potatoes, carrots, cabbage and celery about 15 or 20 minutes. Add corn, beans, peas, onion, salt, oil and tomato juice. Cook 15 minutes or until onion is done.

title: bubble pizza
directions: Cut dough biscuits into quarters.
Individually, coat with sauce.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese and toppings.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: a b's spicy grilled chicken
directions: Cut breasts in half.
In a shallow bowl, combine oil, mustard and sauces (salt and pepper).
Coat chicken with mixture.
Grill or broil 6 to 8 inches from heat source for 10 to 20 minutes until cooked through, turning 2 to 3 times.
Serves 4.

title: 5 can soup
directions: Mix, heat and serve over frito corn chips. May brown ground beef or sausage and add to mixture.

title: chocolate kahlua cheesecake
directions: Combine the four crust ingredients, mixing well.
Firmly press mixture into bottom and sides of a 9 inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 5 minutes.
Let cool.

title: judy's special burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into patties.
Cook on grill for best results (not in frying pan).
Makes approximately 20 (1/4 pound) burgers.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, dry mustard, salt and pepper. Warm ingredients until sugar is melted.
Stir until well blended and pour over carrots.
Cool and serve.
Will keep up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Boil water; add oats and butter (set aside).
Combine brown sugar, white sugar and eggs; add vanilla, cinnamon and sifted flour.
Stir in oatmeal mixture.
Pour into greased and floured rectangular pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: In a brandy snifter, layer cake, pudding, strawberries, walnuts, coconut and whip cream.
In between each layer, put Amaretto.
Then start another layer with cake.
On top of the whole dessert, put whipping cream and strawberries.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Melt margarine and shortening.
Add sugars and mix well.
Add egg; beat until light colored.
Sift flour with soda; stir into egg mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Chill.
Roll in small balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes. Remove at once.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: beef roll-up
directions: After sauteing onions add other vegetables.
Cut beef to make roll.
In each place cheese with onion mixture on top; then roll up and secure with toothpick.
Saute meat well in butter.
Make gravy and serve with noodles on rice.

title: holiday rice
directions: Cook onion, celery, and bell pepper in butter in heavy skillet until tender.
Add rice, salt, broccoli and parsley.
Stir well.
Pour into warm buttered ring mold and turn out on tray, or shape your own ring.
Serve with bowl of beef curry, shrimp creole, or your favorite entree in center of ring.	Garnish with silvered almonds and parsley.
Serves 8.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugars.
Beat well.
Add eggs; beat again. Add flour, mixed with baking powder, soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients; will be very stiff (mix with hands).
Drop by 1/2 spoonfuls on ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: monterey jack mexican dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread in bottom of 8 x 8-inch or 10-inch quiche plate.
Then spoon chili on top of cheese evenly. Grate Monterey cheese evenly over chili and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then use tortilla chips as dippers.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients lightly but thoroughly.
Shape in 2-inch balls and roll in flour.
Brown on all sides in margarine. Add 1 1/2 cups bouillon and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Mix 1/4 cup flour with remaining bouillon until smooth.
Stir into mixture and cook, stirring gently until thickened.
Serves 6.

title: low fat orange dream cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle crumbs onto bottom of 8-9 inch pie plate. Spray with cooking spray. Add Jell-o to boiling water, stir until dissolved. Let cool for 5 minutes. Add cottage cheese and cream cheese and mix with blender on medium until well blended. Add Cool Whip stir gently until blended. Pour over crumbs in pie pan and smooth. Refrigerate for 4 hours or until set.

title: imperial sugar's canefest pralines
directions: Combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt in a 3 1/2-quart heavy saucepan.
Cook for about 5 minutes over high heat or to 210° on a candy thermometer.
Stir often, scraping the bottom of the pan.
The mixture will foam up.
Add margarine and pecans. Continue cooking over medium heat, stirring constantly, and scraping the sides and bottom of pan until the candy reaches the soft-ball stage (234° on the candy thermometer).
Remove from the heat and cool slightly for about 2 minutes.
Beat with a spoon until thick and creamy.
Next, drop a tablespoon of the mixture onto a sheet of waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Let the pralines cool completely.
Makes 20 (2-inch) pralines.

title: lattice top chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crescent rolls.
Save some cheese for top and also 1/2 onion.
Place in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Unwrap crescent rolls; separate into two rectangles.
Press together perforated cuts.
Cut each rectangle lengthwise into 3 strips.
Place strips on casserole to form lattice top.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes longer.
Top lattice with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 3 to 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: cheesy biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop teaspoons of mixture into ungreased mini muffin pans.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yield: 2 dozen.

title: cheese and sausage dip
directions: Cook meat and drain well.
Put in crock-pot.
Add all the ingredients with Velveeta cut in small chunks.
Cook on high until melted down.
Turn to low.
Stir often to keep from burning. (Yes!
It will burn in a crock-pot.)

title: fish stew
directions: Pour 1/4 to 1/2 inch milk in glass baking dish with fish fillets. Bake, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes, depending on thickness of fillets. Pour milk off of fish and sprinkle bread crumbs and dots of butter on fish. Place under broiler 2 to 3 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package direction.
Drain well; rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
In small bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, sugar and seasoning.
In large bowl, combine pasta, dressing and remaining ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: hawaiian casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles in salted, boiling water until tender.

Drain and rinse. Melt 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan while noodles cook. Stir in flour and gradually add milk and pineapple syrup. Stir constantly until thickened. Add pineapple cubes, ham and cooked noodles. Blend well and pour into greased casserole. Combine bread crumbs with 2 tablespoons melted butter and top casserole with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Pour mixture into cartons and freeze.
Thirty minutes before serving time, set cartons out to slightly thaw.

title: tri-hi meat loaf
directions: Combine 1/2 cup cracker crumbs with beef, tomato paste, eggs, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Pat half the mixture into the bottom of square pan.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup cracker crumbs with cottage cheese, mushrooms and parsley.
Spread over meat mixture in dish.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix and line pie pan.
Put in refrigerator 15 minutes or more before filling.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Use blender or mixer.
Put all ingredients in whichever you choose.
Run on mix until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into two oiled 9-inch
pie pans.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes on middle rack
of
oven,
or
until slightly brown.	Prick with fork.

title: tomato and salmon bisque(soup)
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and saute until clear.
Add flour and cook until light brown.
Add water, tomato puree, salmon
and parsley.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add milk and simmer for 15 minutes.
Before serving, add pepper and salt to taste.
Serves 6.

title: grilled tomato halves
directions: Cut tomatoes in half and place in shallow pan, cut side up. Combine remaining ingredients well and spread on tomatoes.
Bake in a 450° oven 8 to 10 minutes or until tops are lightly browned.

title: no fail fudge
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme and chocolate pieces, stirring, until well mixed.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: corn pudding
directions: Can be assembled in pan in which it is to be baked.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Break in eggs and beat with fork.
Add milk and stir until blended.
Stir in corn; scrape onion into mixture and stir until smooth.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn and put in large brown paper bag. Mix brown sugar, margarine and Karo in medium bowl. Cook in microwave on High for 3 minutes. Stir. Cook another 2 minutes on High. Stir in baking soda. Pour mixture over popcorn. Microwave the bag for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Shake well and allow to sit 5 minutes before enjoying.

title: easy peach delight
directions: Pour canned peaches, undrained, into 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of peaches.
Pour melted butter or margarine over cake mix and peaches.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until topping is crunchy and brown. Serve with whipped topping.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Press mixture evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: poor man's pudding
directions: Cover bottom of baking pan with split-open cold biscuits.
Add sugar over and between biscuits.
Cover each biscuit with butter. Cover biscuits with plenty of milk with flavoring in it.
Sprinkle with just a dash of salt.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a large casserole dish, layer the vegetables in order.
Mix sour cream and Miracle Whip and spread over the top of the vegetables.
Garnish with cheese and bacon.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in small pan about 5 minutes; drain well.
Mix with soup, egg, cheese and margarine.
Pour into a baking dish. Top with crushed crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at
350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: country-style potato patties
directions: Mix ingredients in mixing bowl.
Shape into cakes and brown in a small amount of shortening.

title: baked grits
directions: Mix ingredients into grits while still hot.
Place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Set electric skillet at 380°.
Boil sugar, milk, and butter 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat; add marshmallows, vanilla, and peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square pan.

title: st. joseph's chicken dinner cole slaw
directions: Just mix and serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve in a hollowed out loaf of New York seeded rye (large round loaf).
Cube the cut out bread and arrange around loaf.
Also serve with cut fresh vegetables.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Mix up more Tang, put a cherry in each ice cube tray section.
Pour Tang in trays and freeze.
Add to punch.

title: tamale pie
directions: Chop and saute onion and pepper in a little water.
Add next 4 ingredients and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add other ingredients.
Olives are nice if left whole.
Pour into casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Will be firmer if made a day ahead and refrigerated.
Freezes well.
Just heat through to serve.

title: raspberry-jello-rhubarb cake
directions: Mix jello and sugar and place in well-buttered cake pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
On top of jello-sugar mixture, put the rhubarb.
Over the layer of rhubarb, place the marshmallows.
Next, take cake mix and follow directions for mixing.
Pour cake batter over top of marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
The cake comes out when cut into squares the color of the jello that cooks up into it. Delicious.

title: mushroom sausage casserole
directions: Saute onions, sausage and garlic until golden brown in oil. Cut sausage links into 3.
Pour in tomato paste, tomato sauce, mushrooms (with juice) and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: stuffed pizza
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook and stir sausage and ground beef until brown.
Drain; set aside.

title: river bottom pie
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts and press together in large square pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Sift sugar, cornstarch and cocoa together.
Add to eggs.
Mix well.
Add melted oleo and mix well, then add Pet milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.

title: lemon broiled scallops
directions: Preheat broiler.
Place scallops in a shallow baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients.
Baste scallops with one-half of this mixture.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn scallops and baste with remaining sauce.
Broil 5 minutes more. Serves 2.

title: allgood whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar for 10 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour.
Fold in whipping cream that is whipped.
Fold in flavoring (1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon lemon).
Bake in large tube pan.

title: pastry for fried pies
directions: Mix well and roll out on floured board.
Use a saucer to cut out for pies so they will all be the same size.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Combine everything except macaroni; boil and stir.
Add macaroni.
Better the second day.

title: fancy burrito supreme
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, lay out burritos.
Pour chili over burritos (if substituting hamburger and tomato soup, pour over at this time).
Sprinkle taco seasoning on burritos. Sprinkle onion, olives and half the cheese on.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Before serving, put lettuce, sour cream, cheese, tomato and olive on top.
Cut burritos in 1/2 and serve.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Put cucumber and onion in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and mix.
Let stand 2 hours or more.
Drain.
DO NOT RINSE.
Heat vinegar and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Drop onion and dill seed in hot vinegar.
Reheat to just before boiling.
DO NOT BOIL. Put in containers to cool and freeze.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Brown the beef.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Mix salt and pepper with flour in a small bowl.
Mix ketchup and mustard with water.
In a 2-quart casserole, place a layer of potatoes, a layer of carrots and 1/3 of the beef.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of the flour mix on it.
Continue to layer the rest of the meat, vegetables and flour.
Pour the water over the vegetables.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and continue to bake until vegetables are tender and top is browned.
(You can put a crust on top when you remove the foil and bake until crust is brown.)

title: chicken and broccoli braid
directions: Pre-heat oven to 375°F.

title: stuffed strawberries
directions: Mix pudding and milk; fold in the Cool Whip and almond extract. Wash strawberries in cold water; drain well and de-cap.
From the point, slit each into quarters, but do not cut through to the bottom.
Fill with mix and serve.
You may also use the pudding mixture as a dip for strawberries and other fruits.

title: friendship cake
directions: Cream greetings and smiles thoroughly, then add handshakes, beaten separately.
Add love slowly.
Serve with sympathy and hospitality and fold in carefully.
Bake with moderation and serve to all acquaintances.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: *Or 2 teaspoons of either.

title: georgia pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with a wire whisk.
Add flour to granulated sugar. After you have done this, mix all ingredients together by hand. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes. (If pie is not set in middle after 40 minutes, bake a little longer.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Pour in greased bread pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mama's raisin-spice cake
directions: Grease and flour a large tube pan.
Cream the butter and sugar; add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Save a little of the flour mixture to flour the raisins.
Add these last of all.
Bake at 325° for approximately an hour or until a straw inserted comes out clean.

title: potato candy
directions: Mash potato and blend in butter and sugar.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on waxed paper and roll candy out on it in a rectangle.
Spread with peanut butter; roll up and chill.
When chilled, slice and serve.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and bake unwrapped and unpeeled at 500° for 45 minutes.
Slice off top of potato lengthwise and discard.
With large spoon, carefully remove inside of potato and place in mixing bowl.
Set skins aside.
Add sour cream, butter, garlic salt and cheese together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and spoon mixture into potato skins.
Top with chives and reheat until cheese melts at 350°.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and serve while hot.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Mix soup and butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add pork chops. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes a delicious gravy.

title: oreo surprise
directions: First Layer:
Crumbled Oreo cookies and margarine.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Heat about 3/4-inch oil in flat pan like a large skillet. Swirl in oil with funnel.
Hold finger over hole to fill funnel. Brown on one side then flip and brown on other side.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: baked corn
directions: Use juice from corn.
Mix salt, pepper, corn, cornstarch, juice and water together.
Put into baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
(Check often!)

title: black-eye pea soup
directions: Soak peas in water overnight.
Brown bacon in soup pot.
Add onion, carrots and celery.
Cook until just soft. Add garlic and kale.
Cook one minute longer.
Add the broth and water.
Drain peas and add to pot.
Add hot sauce, seasonings and parsley. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 90 minutes (or until peas are soft.)
Add sherry, stir and serve hot.
Crusty french bread goes well or croutons sprinkled lightly on top.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and pan-fry, until golden brown on both sides.
Serve with sausages and/or sour cream or butter or catsup or applesauce.

title: no-bake peanut oat cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in medium saucepan.
Add milk and butter; put over medium heat and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto foiled sheet pan.
Let stand until firm and cold.

title: crab and clam casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; top with bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until bubbly.

title: berry lemonade
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Pour into a pitcher.
Stir in cold water and add ice.

title: grainola cereal
directions: Mix in microwave bowl. Coat everything thoroughly with the honey. Cook in microwave 6 minutes. Stir every 2 minutes. Put out on cookie sheet to cool. Store in plastic airtight bag or container.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown the pork chops. Put a layer of Minute rice to cover bottom of your casserole. Place chops on top of rice. Pour mushroom soup over chops. Add 1 cup water and bake until chops are tender.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar, eggs, and vanilla. Beat until creamy. Add cocoa, flour. Beat well. Add nuts. Bake in 9 x 13 oiled pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and spread marshmallow cream on top while hot. Once cake has cooled, spread on icing.

title: spaghetti red
directions: Crumble hamburger in skillet.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper.
Brown hamburger until vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Add sauce mix, tomato sauce and beans.
Let simmer while you cook the spaghetti as directed on package.
Drain the spaghetti and mix with meat sauce.

title: pork piquant
directions: Buy a 4 pound loin or pork rib end and have your butcher bone and cut it into chops.
You should have at least 9 thick chops from this amount.
Cut excess fat from the chops; otherwise, the sauce will be greasy.
Sear the chops until brown and put in the bottom of a shallow 3-quart casserole dish.
Season with about 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.

title: yummy cupcakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: won't last long cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Stir in pineapple, bananas, nuts and vanilla.
Mix in order and pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cake will freeze well.
This cake is very good and moist.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Dissolve baking soda in warm water; set aside.
In large bowl, combine applesauce, sugar, flour, oil, spices and salt.
Add baking soda mixture. Fold in nuts and fruit.
Spread batter in preheated pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Test with tester at 1 hour.

title: monkey bars
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar on top while still hot.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: delicious fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Whisk together milk, sugar and flour. Pour in dish. Spoon pie filling over mixture.
Do not mix. Bake uncovered 30 minutes until cobbler is golden brown on top.

title: holy guacamole
directions: Peel and mash 1 avocado. Mix with lemon juice, cilantro, garlic, basil and salt. Dice remaining avocado. Fold into mixture with red pepper, salsa and green onion. Garnish with sour cream. Serve with tortilla chips and fresh vegetables.
Makes 1 1/2 cups guacamole.

title: creole liver(a family favorite for 40 years!)
directions: Saute bacon in skillet until nearly crisp.
Remove bacon and set aside.
Dredge liver with flour and brown in bacon fat with the diced onions.
Add bacon and all the remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: john's cole slaw dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Serve over shredded cabbage.

title: garlic roasted chicken and potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in an 17 x 11-inch pan.
Cut potatoes into bite sized chunks.
Place chicken, potatoes and garlic in roasting pan. Turn ingredients to coat with oleo.
Place chicken skin side up. At 350°, bake 40 minutes.
In bowl, mix maple syrup and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Brush chicken and potatoes with mix.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: barbara's potato surprise
directions: Cut uncooked potatoes into thin, round slices.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese, in a skillet. The type and amount of dressing and Polish sausage is your choice.
Fry until potatoes are done.
After this is done, top with cheese and return to heat just until cheese is melted.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix reserved juice with enough water to make 1 cup.
Cream the butter and 1/2 cup of sugar until light and fluffy.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon drained fruit over batter.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of sugar, then juice.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with cream.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Saute onions, garlic and chili powder in margarine over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until onion is tender.
Stir in catchup, brown sugar, dry mustard, salt, water, and vinegar. Remove from heat; set aside.
Remove any visible fat from chicken. Dip chicken into sauce mixture to coat both sides.
Arrange in a single layer in a large roasting pan or baking dish.
Spoon any remaining sauce over chicken.
Bake at 375° for about 50 minutes or until done.
Baste once or twice during the baking.
Serves 8 people.
250 calories each portion.

title: sweet potato pineapple casserole
directions: Butter baking dish, place 1/2 of mixture in dish, dot with marshmallows, then add remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven, dot with marshmallows and replace in oven until brown.

title: egg surprise
directions: Prepare day before serving.
Combine sausage, soup, cheese and mushrooms.
Lay in eggs.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.

title: fruit salad(macaroni rings)
directions: Cook macaroni rings.
Drain.
Boil together sugar, salt, flour, pineapple juice, lemon juice and eggs.
Pour over macaroni rings. Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Add fruit.
Whip 1 pint of whipping cream.
Mix all together.
Nuts and marshmallows can be added if desired.

title: caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until well blended. Add eggs and mix until blended. Melt caramels with milk on low heat, stirring frequently until smooth. Stir in pecans. Pour caramel mixture into crust and top with cream cheese batter. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool and refrigerate.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add
eggs, one at a time.
Add vinegar, vanilla and pecans.
Beat	well.
Pour
into
unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 or 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: mammaw's corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Put in a cast-iron skillet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until golden.

title: peanut butter-n-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the butter, sugars and peanut butter in a large bowl with mixer on medium speed, until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes, remove from cookie sheets. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Then mix the remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture on top of bottom layer.
Sprinkle entire top of cake with the 1/2 cup of remaining powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until slightly brown.
If desired, one may sprinkle 1/4 cup chopped pecans on top of powdered sugar prior to baking.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Combine all ingredients except wraps; place 1 teaspoon of filling in center of each wrap.
Moisten edges with water; fold each skin in half to form triangle, pressing edges to seal.
Pull bottom corners of triangles down to overlap slightly.
Moisten one corner with water and press to seal, pushing out excess air.
Fry a few at a time in oil at 375°; drain.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients into a loaf and place in long Pyrex or aluminum baking pan.
Combine the 5 ingredients for sauce and pour over loaf.
Meat loaf may be basted with sauce about halfway through baking.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bowl, break the eggs up (take shells off).
Flour next, vanilla, sugar.
Mix up with a spoon and stir up real fast, mix up good, butter cinnamon, chocolate drops.
Then sugar - stir a little bit more.
Put in two circle pans.
Heat oven to 400°; don't want to burn it, cook 3 minutes until done.
Then ice, and eat, and then go brush teeth, watch TV and go to bed.
Don't forget to read a book!

title: barbecued steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except steak in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer gently for 5 minutes.
Pound steak.
Cut into serving size portions.
Place in large roasting pan.
Pour hot sauce over meat.
Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Tie spices in small cloth bag.
Combine cider, brown sugar and salt in kettle.
Add spice bag.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cocoa fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and vanilla and beat with wire whisk until thoroughly blended.
Cook on low flame until slightly thickened, then add vanilla and margarine.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust and top with meringue and brown.

title: frozen lemon pudding
directions: Chill evaporated milk in ice tray or bowl in an ice bowl until ice cold. Mix egg yolks, 6 tablespoons of sugar, lemon rind and 2 tablespoons of lemon juice in large bowl.

title: anything goes salad
directions: Take Eagle Brand milk and add cherry pie filling and pineapple.
Mix into softened Cool Whip.

title: chocolate skillet pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa. Beat egg yolks and add milk.

Melt butter in skillet; stir dry mixture into butter until well mixed. Remove from heat; stir in liquid mixture and return to heat. Stir over heat until thick. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue. Bake slowly until browned.

title: macaroni and cheese pie
directions: Mix milk, eggs and pepper to taste.
Cook macaroni and drain. Mix in cheese and stir around until melted.
Place in a dish and pour in milk and eggs.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In large bowl mix all together.
Chill until serving time.

title: double good macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain. Combine remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot glazed chicken breasts and thighs
directions: Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Spoon apricot preserves over chicken.
Pour Catalina dressing over chicken.
Place uncovered in 350° preheated oven. Baste sauce from dish every 20 minutes over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour or until chicken is cooked to your preference.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients
with
oleo.
Take out one cup of crumbs to sprinkle over the top of cake.
Add molasses, water, hot
water and soda mixture.
Mix thoroughly.	Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cool veggie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place 1 package crescent roll dough on baking sheet.
Press seams together so that it bakes in a solid piece.
Bake until golden brown (about 10 minutes).
Mix cream cheese and dressing mix.
Spread mixture over cooled dough.
Top with vegetables.
Slice and serve.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: In a large skillet cook green pepper or onion in 1 tablespoon of margarine or butter till tender.
Add eggs; cook over medium heat without stirring till mixture begins to set on bottom and around edge.
Lift and fold partially cooked eggs so uncooked portion flows beneath.
Continue cooking till just set.
Transfer to 1 quart casserole.

title: banana split
directions: Mix Corn Chex, melted butter and sugar together.
Let sit overnight and then pat into a casserole pan (9 x 11-inch).
Mix confectioners sugar, egg and butter together on medium speed. Layer on top of Corn Chex mixture.
Layer the pineapple next, followed by the bananas (sliced), whipped cream, cherries and nut pieces.
Keep cool. Cut and serve.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix first seven ingredients together.
Press mixture into firm cakes (8 to 10).
Chill well.
Before serving, dip cakes in flour, then in egg beaten with water, then dip into bread crumbs.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Saute cakes quickly over high heat until brown, turning once.

title: stack-ups
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, peppers, chili powder and salt.
Simmer 10 minutes. Layer tortillas.
Spread with beans, meat sauce and cheese, 4 to a stack.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground meat until brown.
Drain.
Stir in Hamburger Helper, water, chili powder, garlic and cayenne pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring often.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring often for 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes.
Place lettuce, green peppers, tomatoes, onions and olives in a large bowl.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate until chilled at least 4 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips and sour cream.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl and mix well by hand. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. The batter will stay good up to 6 weeks in the refrigerator. Bake the amount you want in a greased muffin pan. Makes 48 muffins.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and coconut.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in greased or paper lined muffin pans.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and lemon juice.
Mix in eggs.
Stir in rhubarb and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; dot with butter and bake in a 400° oven until done.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix cooking oil, sugar and eggs.
Add milk, vanilla, food coloring, then add all dry ingredients.
Bake in oblong pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate oreo dessert
directions: Combine and mix cookie crumbs and butter in bowl.
Press into 9 x 14-inch pan.
Slice ice cream and press over cookie mixture. Spread with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup and top with pecans.
Cover with foil; freeze for several hours.

title: crab delight cocktail spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and crab meat; mound on plate.
Top with cocktail sauce and garnish with parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: gotombki(stuffed cabbage)
directions: Core the cabbage deep.
Pour 1 cup of water into the core cavity.
Cover with a plastic bag and place into a microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Open plastic bag carefully and check the cabbage leaves for softness.
Removes leaves one at a time.
If they don't remove easily, add more water.
Cover and microwave again.
Time varies according to microwave.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Blend thoroughly.
Enough dressing for 1 large grated cabbage.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat first 5 ingredients till smooth. Gradually add next 4 ingredients. Continue to beat with electric beater till smooth.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: buffet vegetable casserole
directions: Drain beans, chestnuts and corn.
Mix first 12 ingredients and place in large buttered casserole.
Crumble 1/2 of Cheese Nips and mix with 1/2 stick butter or margarine and 1/4 cup sliced almonds. Place atop casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas, sugar, butter and eggs together.
Mix together flour, soda and salt and stir into banana mixture.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Bake in loaf or Bundt pan 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Do not overbake.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix chili powders, cumin and oregano in small bowl and stir in 1/2 cup water to form thick paste; set aside. Toss beef cubes with 2 teaspoons salt in large bowl; set aside.

title: nachos
directions: Place chips on a baking sheet.
Spread refried beans on each; top with cheese, salsa and pepper slices.
Broil on low until cheese melts and nachos are lightly browned.
Top with a little sour cream and serve hot.

title: scallops - baked
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Add next five ingredients and mix.
Add bread crumbs.
Arrange 6 scallops in each of 8 sea shells or small individual casseroles.
Top each with 1 tablespoon crumb mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 500° for five minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add cheese.
After cheese melts, stir in sour cream, salt and pepper.
Boil potatoes with skins on, then skin them and grate at medium holes of grater.
Fold cheese mixture into the grated potatoes.
Put some grated cheese on top. Bake 1 hour at 300°, uncovered.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix beef, spaghetti sauce, water and salt.
Heat until bubbly. Mix Ricotta cheese, eggs, pepper and 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese.
Stuff manicotti shells with mixture.
If you microwave, these do not have to be cooked beforehand, but if using a regular oven, do cook manicotti shells first according to package directions.

title: spam sandwich spread
directions: Grind spam and eggs in meat grinder (I use a food processor). Stir and add Miracle Whip, a small amount of mustard and horse radish sauce (if desired).

title: fabulous cheesecake
directions: Grease 9-inch spring-form pan.
In larger mixer bowl, at high speed, beat cream cheese with Ricotta cheese until creamy and well combined.
Gradually beat in sugar, then eggs until well combined. At low speed, beat in cornstarch, flour, lemon juice and vanilla. Add melted butter and sour cream.
Beat until just smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, Hershey's syrup and flour.
Beat together well.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before frosting.

title: peach pie alaska
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add ice cream.
Stir until melted. Blend in Cool Whip and fruit.
Spoon into baked pie crust.

title: andy's homemade peas
directions: Heat to a boil and serve.

title: spicy new england corned beef
directions: Place brisket, fat side down, in roasting pan in about 1/2-inch of water.
Seal
pan with heavy foil and cook at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours until tender,
keeping small amount of water in pan.
When brisket is done, drain liquid from roasting pan and pour into a large stock pot.
Make a paste with brown sugar and mustard.
Spoon glaze over and under brisket.
Return to oven at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Garnish with shredded carrots, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: texas soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix the chili beans, corn, mixed vegetables, onion soup, salt, pepper and chili powder to drained hamburger.
Stir in extra water to desired thickness.

title: chicago italian beef
directions: Cut 1 medium sized elephant into small bite-sized pieces. Takes about 1 month!
Add enough gravy to cover; salt and pepper and cook over kerosene stove at 465° for 4 weeks.
Serves 3800 people.
If more are expected, add 2 rabbits.
However, add rabbits only if necessary because most people do not like "hare" in their stew.

title: san antonio pasta skillet
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, over medium heat, cook onions, green pepper and garlic in oil for 2 minutes.
Add pasta.
Cook, stirring 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, broth, turkey/chicken, picante sauce and cumin.
Simmer 3 minutes, stirring occasionally and breaking up tomatoes with a spoon, and continue to simmer 4 to 5 minutes, until pasta is tender and most of the liquid is absorbed.
Sprinkle with cheese and cilantro.
Serve with additional picante sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bill paul's salmon patties
directions: Remove bones from salmon.
Mix together and shape in four patties.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Brown beef. Add mushrooms, garlic and oregano. Stir-fry about 5 minutes. Add spinach and heat until thawed and juices are cooked away (about 10). Spoon into buttered casserole dish and scatter cheese on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, grated zucchini and vanilla and mix lightly.
Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder; mix lightly.
Add nuts; mix lightly. Pour into two wax paper-lined loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cheese balls(makes 3)
directions: Let soften; mix together by hand and form into balls.
Roll in crushed nuts or parsley.

title: herb flavored pork chops
directions: Beat egg and milk until blended.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese.
Dip pork chops in crumbs, then in egg mixture, then in crumbs again.
Brown chops in hot oil.
Pour off drippings.
Spoon mushroom soup over chops.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: debbie's chicken casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, layer ingredients starting with cooked rice, bite size pieces of cooked chicken, 1 cup cooked broccoli and 1/2 of the Velveeta cheese, cut in squares.
Mix soup with can of water in another bowl and pour 1/2 over cheese.
Repeat layers with leftover ingredients (save as before).
Cook at 350° for about 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cook chicken breasts and set aside.
Fry vegetables with garlic and drain.
Combine vegetables with other ingredients and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Prepare 2 boxes chicken flavored rice; serve chicken over.

title: lethal jello
directions: Add jello and gelatin to boiling water.
Stir and let stand 5 minutes.
Add liquor.
Stir and pour into glass pan. Cool until firm and cut into squares.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and 1/2 onion; drain.
Stir in 1/2 package taco seasoning (all for spicier) and 3/4 cup water; simmer.
In separate pan, put tomato paste, 3 cans water and package of enchilada mix.
Bring to a boil.
Dip flour shells in sauce. Place in greased dish and fill center with hamburger, onion and green chilies.
Roll up and turn seam side down.
Pour remaining sauce over and add necessary amount of canned sauce to cover.
Top with mixture of Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheese (grated).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill if desired or heat.

title: beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle beef brisket with Lawry's seasoned salt on both sides. Place in casserole dish with cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
If dry, add water.
Slice onion on top of beef; use a whole big onion. Cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours more.
Remove from oven and let set in juices in refrigerator overnight.

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix celery, cheese and crackers together in a bowl.
Mix tomato juice and salad dressing together.
Pour over celery mixture and blend together.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg, milk and vanilla and beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually and mix well.
Shape a teaspoon of dough into balls.
Roll balls in sugar; place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a candy Kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down so that the cookie cracks around the edge.
Return the pan to oven; bake 2 to 5 minutes more.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: oven browned potatoes
directions: Wash and peel (or just scrub) potatoes; cut up into evenly sized pieces.
Pour water over potatoes and cook only until water returns to boiling.
Drain.
Dip into melted beef or butter. Drain off excess drippings and put in a shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour on 350° or until brown.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
In a saucepan, melt 1 cup butter and add the 1/3 cup cocoa.
Add the egg mixture and beat well.
Add the pecans.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
As soon as the cake is removed from the oven, cover it with marshmallows.
Return the pan to the oven until marshmallows are slightly melted.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine noodles, tuna, milk, sour cream, mushrooms, chicken soup and pepper in baking dish.
Top with mixture of bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and butter.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Leave cake in pan.
Poke holes in warm cake with fork.
Spread caramel topping on cake while warm; let cool.
Make pudding according to package directions.
Put on cake.
Top pudding with 1/2 of crushed candy.
Top with Cool Whip.
Top with rest of candy.
Refrigerate.

title: western hash
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain off fat.
Add the remaining ingredients, cover and simmer 25 minutes stirring occasionally. Top with Velveeta; heat until melted.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, brown sugar, granulated sugar, egg and water.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and oatmeal. Mix vanilla, walnuts and chocolate chips into batter.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients with desired amount of mayonnaise. Pour into salad bowl.
Chill.
Serve cold.

title: crazy cake
directions: Into ungreased 8 x 10-inch cake pan sift first 5 ingredients. Into the mound of dry ingredients poke 3 holes.
In one drop the vanilla, in another the vinegar and in the last the melted shortening.
Pour the cold water over all and blend well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Can be baked 45 minutes for a drier cake.

title: lemon cream sauce
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick. Add sugar gradually and beat.
Add butter, lemon rind and juice.
Fold this into the whipped cream. Serves 8.

title: turketti
directions: Cook noodles and set aside.
Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Mix together onion, turkey, 3 cups cheese, mushroom soup and pimento.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Toss with cooked noodles. Use a large casserole.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When done, poke hole in top and pour in sherry.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop broccoli and cook until just a little soft but still firm.
Mix together mayo, Cheddar cheese, eggs, soup, onion, salt, pepper and 1 cup Italian bread crumbs. Add broccoli.
Mix well. Pour in
a loaf pan or a casserole dish. Sprinkle Italian bread crumbs on top to suit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Combine 1/2 gallon of cider and spices in large crock-pot. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add remaining cider, lemonade, orange juice and brown sugar.
Heat until very hot, but do not boil.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Cook eggs, sugar and milk until creamy.
Add vanilla, salt, milk and strawberries.
Complete filling to fill line of freezer with milk.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Crumble cake in bottom of glass baking dish (bite size chunks).
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; mix in frozen berries and stir until thawed and Jell-O thickens.
Pour over crumbled cake. Crumble more cake on top of mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up squash and cook in water to which the flavoring packet from the Stove Top has been added.
Cook until squash is tender. Add dry ingredients from Stove Top.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Put in oven or microwave long enough to melt cheese.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O over softened cream cheese.
Mix together until completely blended.
Add boiling water to Jell-O/cream cheese mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Add 7-Up.
Blend again.
Add pineapple with juice.
Add nuts and mix.
Pour into 8 x 11-inch dish.
Chill in refrigerator until set.

title: pumpkin raisin cookies
directions: Beat sugars and liquid Butter Buds until smooth.
Add Egg Beaters, vanilla and pumpkin; mix until well blended.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add the Grape-Nuts and raisins.
Chill dough 30 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°; cool.
Dust with powdered sugar or make a glaze with skim milk and powdered sugar and drizzle over cooled cookies.
Yields 4 1/2 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: ham and rice casserole
directions: Save 1/3 of soup and milk.
Mix remaining soup and milk.
Pour over the rice, pepper and ham in a glass casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over the top.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on the cheese.
Pour saved milk and soup (mixed together) over the casserole.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans deluxe
directions: Cook onion in bacon fat; add to pork and beans.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° until bubbling in center.

title: peanut fondant
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Cook until it hardens when tested in water.
Stir into well beaten egg whites; beat until cool. Roll out on buttered board, then cover with peanut butter.
Roll up and cut out in pieces.
(Roll up as you would jelly roll.)

title: punch
directions: Put 1/4 amount of recipe in each of 4 large Tupperware buckets.
Mix 10 cups of water, 1 large pineapple juice and 1 large lemonade together.
Prepare 1 box of jello and add to mixture.
Dissolve 1 1/4 cups sugar in 1 cup of hot water.
Mix all together and put into freezer.
Stir often after it starts to freeze to make it slushy.
Remove 4 to 6 hours before serving. When ready to serve, add 1/2 bottle almond extract and 1 bottle ginger ale.
Serves 200 people.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (except Cheddar cheese) and refrigerate overnight.
Let casserole stand at room temperature for one hour before baking time.
Cheddar cheese may be sprinkled on the top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sicilian style pizza
directions: Lightly grease 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Evenly pat each loaf into pan, pressing together at center; pinch up edges of dough to form rim.
Spread Prego sauce over dough.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until crust is golden. (Makes 8 servings.)

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken whole; cool, skin, bone and chop.
Set aside. Boil spaghetti; rinse.
Set aside to drain.
Grease bottom and sides of large casserole dish with oleo.
Layer chopped chicken, spaghetti, peas and pimentos.
Slice Velveeta and oleo; scatter on top of pimentos.
Continue until dish is full.
Top with pimentos atop cheese.
Pour broth and 1 cup canned milk over all.
Bake at 350°, covered, until cheese melts and liquid is thick.
If too stiff, add extra milk.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken and broccoli spears.
Mix together cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Use a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Layer chicken first, then broccoli.
Spread on top of broccoli the mixture of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Sprinkle with cheese, then crumbled chips on top.
Cook 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: nonbaked cookies
directions: Microwave the first 4 ingredients for 4 minutes.
Mix and microwave 2 minutes more.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine until tender.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add cheese and cream.
Beat together with wire whisk.
Drain fettuccine.
Mix fettuccine and cheese mixture together well.
Top with 3 ounce package of shredded Parmesan cheese.

title: deep-dish tuna pie
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion and potato in water, covered, about 7 minutes; drain off liquid.
Stir in soup, milk, cheese, lemon juice, dill weed and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Stir in frozen vegetables and tuna.
Spoon into an ungreased 2-quart casserole.

title: mom's homemade noodles
