directions: Mix well.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness on a floured board.
Let dry for about 2 hours, turning once so both sides can dry.
Dust off flour.
Roll as thin as possible.
Cut in thin strips.
Drop into boiling chicken broth.
Cook about 30 minutes.

title: stir-n-drop oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices into bowl.
Add brown sugar and oats.
Mix in oil, milk and egg.
Add nuts or raisins if desired.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with a mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Freeze.
Thaw partially before serving.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Combine with all other ingredients except mushrooms.
Bake in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Pour undrained mushrooms over top of casserole and bake for 15 minutes more.
Recipe can be doubled for large gatherings.

title: angel hair pasta with pine nuts
directions: Place butter in warm serving dish to become very soft.
Brown pine nuts in heavy skillet using no oil (careful they burn easily).
Cook and drain pasta; toss with butter to coat.
Add cheese, pine nuts and pepper and toss.
Serve immediately.

title: easy breakfast
directions: Crumble bread into bottom of oblong cake pan.
Add fried sausage or bacon.
Mix eggs with 2 cups of milk and beat well. Place mixture on top of sausage or bacon.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with a fork.
Blend in sugar, salt and beaten eggs.
Melt butter and stir into banana mixture.
Dissolve soda in water.
Add flour.
Mix and bake in a greased loaf pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Fantastic!
Makes 6 servings.

title: hard candy or lollipops
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310°.
Remove from fire.
After the boiling has ceased, stir in flavoring and food coloring.
Pour into sucker molds or into lightly greased sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: yogurt-orange chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken lightly with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook, turning, until browned on all sides.
Remove chicken and set aside.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Dice.
Mix Velveeta, onion, Ro-Tel, soups and spices.
Crush chips.
Pour 1/2 of chips into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken on top of chips, add Velveeta mixture, then top with remaining chips.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old south pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, nuts and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 50 minutes.
Pecans will float to the top and brown if baked slowly.

title: sugar free apple pie(you'll never miss the sugar!)
directions: Mix peeled and sliced apples with juice, cinnamon and tapioca. Place in pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake 40 to 50 minutes until tender.
(Two crusts can be used, too.)

title: spritz cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix margarine and sugar. Stir in the remaining ingredients. Fill cookie press with dough; form desired shapes on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until set but not brown, 6 to 9 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: peppy stuffed peppers
directions: Halve green peppers lengthwise.
Remove seed and wash peppers. Lightly mix ground beef, rice, onions, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Pile lightly into pepper halves; arrange in baking dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until peppers are tender.

title: nellie's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together; save some noodles for top.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Place apples in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and water.
Top with dry cake mix and dot butter on top.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.
Top with ice cream (optional).

title: dump cake
directions: Dump undrained pineapple into a 9 x 13 inch ungreased pan and spread evenly.
Dump cherry pie filling and spread evenly.
Dump cake mix (dry) over cherry pie filling; spread evenly.
Dump pecans on top.
Slice margarine into pats and place over the top.

title: lift (pickled turnips)
directions: Wash, peel and quarter turnips.
Salt the turnips.
Pack turnips and beets in a gallon jar.
Add 4 tablespoons salt, 1 part vinegar to 1 part lukewarm water enough to cover.
Add approximately 4 hot peppers, if desired.
Seal jar as tight as possible.
Let set 1 week on counter.
Transfer into quart jars and refrigerate.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Pour ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: grandma's home baked beans
directions: Cover beans with cold water and soak overnight.
Drain off. Add hot water and rest of ingredients.
Cook for 4 hours at 250. Add hot water to cover as needed.

title: baked scallops
directions: Melt butter.
Add crackers and bread crumbs; fold in scallops. Put in baking dish and pour cream evenly on top; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: weight watchers bread pudding
directions: For each serving, combine skim milk and egg in deep bowl.
Add sweetener and flavoring to taste and beat with rotary beater until mixed.
Pour into individual Pyrex baking dish.
Tear bread into small pieces; poke each one into the mixture.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Place dish in pan with an inch of water and bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: spiced mixed nuts
directions: Blend spices, egg and water; beat until frothy.
Add nuts, 1/2 cup at a time.
Butter cookie sheet.
Spread nuts in a single layer on cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs with fork, stirring in oil, vanilla, lemon, sugar and flour.
Drop teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Stamp each cookie flat with bottom of glass (oiled) and dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: violet's potato donuts
directions: Mash potatoes well.
Beat in eggs, sugar and soft shortening. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and mace.
Add mashed potatoes.
Chill dough for 2 hours.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together and set aside flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Blend together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Add rolled oats, vanilla and chocolate bits.
Dough is crumbly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet and bake approximately 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 11 dozen.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and put into bowl or mold and refrigerate.

title: beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package. Mix ingredients. Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in large mixing bowl; beat 4 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: western pot roast
directions: Brown roast in oil.
Add chopped onion.
Cook until golden. Combine catsup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour over meat.
Simmer covered until meat is tender, about 3 hours.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Mix ingredients except peaches or pie filling.
Pour into pan.
Pour peaches into batter.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: apple raisin bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 12 muffin cups.
In a large bowl, soak cereal in milk for 5 minutes.
Stir in margarine, honey, apple, raisins, egg and cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
With a rubber spatula, fold flour into bran mixture just enough to moisten.
Do not overmix.
Evenly distribute among muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until done.

title: volcano relish
directions: Chop vegetables.
Put together in bowl; salt.
Set for 3 hours.
Boil vinegar, sugar, turmeric, mustard seed and celery seed.
Add chopped, drained vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Fill jars, using slotted spoon, and seal.
Makes 10 pints.

title: super peanut butter sandwich
directions: Combine peanut butter, cream cheese and honey; mix well. Spread on bread slices.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add tomato paste, taco seasoning, beer and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Place in crock dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in oven or microwave until cheese melts.
Serve with nachos.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix the Cool Whip, cottage cheese and dry jello.
Add pineapple, oranges and nuts; mix well.
Garnish top with nuts. Chill and serve.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator.

title: "red" route 66 chili
directions: Crumble hamburger meat into covered pan.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for 3 hours.
When nearly done, remove lid and let boil down to proper consistency.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with side dishes of Ranch Style beans and diced onion.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hobo bread
directions: Combine raisins, boiling water and baking soda.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, add sugar, flour, oil and walnuts.
Blend well.
Pour into greased 1 pound coffee cans; fill 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes and remove.
Makes 3 loaves.
I use 2 bread pans.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Core tomatoes and cut in half crosswise.
Make shallow crisscross cut on surface of tomatoes. Season cut surface with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with oregano or basil.
Drizzle with salad dressing.
Broil cut side up 3-inches from heat, about 5 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: fudge icing
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and cream in pan and boil for 3 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and mix until melted.

title: mandarin orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add can of frozen orange juice (no water), cans of mandarin oranges and can of crushed pineapple.
Place in refrigerator until set.
Whip Dream Whip and 1/2 of the milk.
In another bowl whip the balance of milk with instant pudding.
Pour both mixtures together in one bowl and whip until thick and fluffy.
Spread on top of jello.

title: finger cookies
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: popover pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown meat and lightly season and drain.
Put in pan.
Top with Ragu to cover.
Sprinkle cheese over Ragu.
Beat together eggs, milk and oil until foamy.
Beat in flour and salt until batter is smooth (it will be thin).
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake for 35 minutes or until crust is puffed and golden brown.

title: sherried chicken
directions: Lightly sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt; brown in butter in heavy skillet.
Transfer to baking dish; pour mushroom liquid and sherry over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and transfer chicken to serving dish.
Measure pan drippings back into skillet and add water if necessary to make 1 1/4 cups liquid.
Blend chicken gravy mix into liquid; bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Blend in sour cream and mushrooms; when sauce is smooth and hot, pour over chicken breasts.
Serve with hot rice.

title: fry chik spread
directions: Combine and let stand overnight.
Serve on toasted bun.

title: refrigerator muffins
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar; add eggs.
Mix in sour cream and then all the other ingredients.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
This mixture keeps well in the refrigerator for several days.
Yields 2 dozen medium size muffins.

title: betty crocker french ribbon loaf
directions: Measure (level measurements) and sift together into a mixing bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Make a well and add in order the egg yolks, water and orange rind.
Beat with spoon until smooth.

title: chocolate cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream butter; add cheese, chocolate and salt.
Blend.
Add sugar alternately with cream, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Spread on white or yellow cake layers.

title: muffin doughnuts
directions: Beal sugar, oil and eggs at high speed.
Add flour, baking powder, nutmeg, salt, milk and vanilla.
Beat at high speed. Grease and flour muffin tins.
Fill little over half full.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
When cool, dip tips and bottoms in melted butter, then in a cinnamon and sugar mixture.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except rice, in casserole dish.
Heat in oven until bubbling at 400°.
Mix in rice and cook 5 minutes.

title: mary fannie's tea cakes
directions: Mix well; roll out like biscuits.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 425° until slightly brown.

title: shrimp and brown gravy over white rice
directions: Note:
This is a dish that most shrimp captains cook while at sea; it's easy and really good.

title: heart healthy pepper steak
directions: Broil steak on a rack until rare; cut into thin strips.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add red pepper strips and saute until tender. Add steak, broth and soy sauce and cook for 3 minutes.
Gradually stir in dissolved cornstarch and cook until sauce thickens. Season with pepper.
Makes 2 servings.

title: make ahead breakfast egg bake
directions: Cube bread and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer cheese, mushrooms, onion and meat.
Combine eggs, milk and salt in blender, processor or mixer.
Add dry mustard and paprika and blend.
Pour over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until silver knife inserted in center comes clean.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Boil until tender without salt.
Drain all but 1/2 cup water.
Mix all together.
Bake 3 to 4 hours at 300°.
(Can cook all day in crock-pot too!)
Can double recipe.

title: quick-baked pasta family style
directions: Bring 4 quarts water to boil.
Heat a large frying pan and add the oil, beef and garlic.
Saute until the meat is tender and then drain excess fat.
Add all remaining ingredients except cheese for topping.
Add pasta to water.
Simmer the mixture while pasta cooks until just barely tender.
Drain pasta and mix it with the sauce.
Pour all into 3 quart glass rectangle dish and top with the remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes. Great to freeze then microwave.

title: mince meat
directions: Put meat through grinder; dice apples.
Cook until apples are soft; then add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook in wine or cider.
Can or freeze.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Shell and devein shrimp, leaving fan tail on.
Combine all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Dip shrimp in mixture.
Place in shallow pan in single layer.
Pour remaining mixture over shrimp.
Broil 6 to 8 minutes 3 inches from heat.

title: fruit pie
directions: Cook in saucepan until thick.
Add large package of Jell-O; let cool.
Add 1/2 cup of pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Add Dream Whip or Cool Whip on top.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Mix cranberries, apples, pineapple and sugar.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple juice.
Chill until partially set. Mix in cranberries, apples, pineapple mixture and nuts.
Place pineapple slices on top.
Chill until firm.
May be poured into individual molds.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 or 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ribbon cake
directions: Mix 1 cup applesauce with the green Jell-O and 1 cup applesauce with the red Jell-O.
Set aside.
Layer the graham crackers and alternate Jell-O mixtures, ending with graham crackers.
Mix the Dream Whip with milk and almond extract.
Whip until fluffy.
Cover top layer of graham crackers.
Refrigerate. Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, chocolate, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Dissolve
yeast
and
sugar in lukewarm water.
Combine soda and buttermilk.
Mix flour and Crisco oil.
Combine the 3 mixtures and mix well.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Roll on floured surface
and cut.
Cook
as
many as needed.
Keep dough well covered
in container
in
refrigerator;
will
keep 2 weeks. Brush with melted butter just before baking.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Makes 35 biscuits.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer chicken and vegetables.
Mix soup and broth; pour on chicken and vegetable mixture.
Mix butter, milk and Bisquick in bowl; pour on top of soup and other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots; add drained squash and onions.
Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread 1/2 the stuffing mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture over the top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing over the top of the vegetables mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter and add onion and mushrooms; saute 5 minutes. Stir in soups and sherry.
Cook on medium heat until hot.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and stir.
Stir in milk over low heat. Add cheese and salt.
Stir until cheese is melted.
If too thick, may add a little more milk.

title: warm water devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add cocoa.
Blend well.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Put soda in flour.
Add milk along with flour. Add warm water last.
Bake in moderate oven at 350°.
Frost with your favorite fudge icing.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix sauerkraut, carrots, celery, green pepper, onion and pimentos.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and salt until it boils to soft ball stage (about 10 minutes).
Combine remaining ingredients in a separate bowl.
Pour boiled mixture over top; blend together.
Pour into greased pan (approximately 15 x 11 x 1-inch).
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: pear preserves
directions: Peel pears and cut in medium slices.
Pour sugar over pears. Soak overnight.
In large boiler cook at medium heat until pears turn light brown in color.
Put in sterile jars.
Seal tight.

title: 5 hour meal
directions: Place meat, potatoes, carrots and onions in heavy pot.
Mix soups and water and pour over top of meat and vegetables.
Cover. Bake at 250° to 300° for 5 hours.

title: sweet and sour smokies
directions: Mix all together and simmer on top of stove for 1 hour or in crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done. Mix uncooked broccoli, mayonnaise, sour cream, onion, broccoli, soups and cheese until all ingredients are thoroughly coated and wet.

title: doubly chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: marshmallow dip
directions: Soften both Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese.
Mix and serve with fruit for appetizer.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix beef, sausage, bread crumbs, egg, onion and salt.
Shape into 24 balls.
Brown and drain off fat.
Combine soup, water and garlic and pour over meatballs.
Cover and cook over low heat, 20 minutes.
Serve on rolls.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine chicken, soup, broth and vegetables.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining 1/2 of crust.
Return to oven and continue baking until brown.
Total cooking time is approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: beef 'n biscuit casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Simmer while preparing dough.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits, then pull those apart into 2 layers.
Press 10 biscuits layering over bottom of ungreased 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Combine 1/2 cup cheese (saving rest for topping), sour cream and egg.
Mix well.
Remove meat from heat; stir in sour cream mixture; spoon over dough.
Arrange remaining biscuit layers on top; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until the biscuits are deep golden brown.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan, bring to a boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
Brown 1 pound ground beef in 2 tablespoons butter; add to sauce.
(Good sauce for sliced beef, also.)

title: applesauce(chunky)
directions: Combine apples and water in a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole dish with a lid.
Cover and microwave on High for 4 minutes or until apples and pears are tender, stirring 1/2 through cooking time.
Stir in sugar, lemon peel, and cinnamon.
Cover and microwave on High for 2 to 4 minutes until sugar dissolves.
Stir well.

title: macaroni and cheese salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse with cold water.
Add vinegar. Mix lightly and let stand 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients except pepper rings to mayonnaise to blend.
Put pepper rings over the top.

title: triple layer jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and extract. Chill until slightly thickened, about 1 1/2 hours.
Measure 1/3 cup and pour into 4 cup mold.
Chill; about 5 minutes.
Measure 3/4 cup jello; blend into 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Carefully spoon into mold. Chill about 5 minutes.
Add peaches to remaining jello.
Carefully spoon into mold.
Chill 4 hours over overnight.
Dip container into warm water to unmold.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip and additional fruit.

title: skillet burgers
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook meat until loses color.
Drain off grease.
Add all ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup of catsup and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each.
Add flour mixture with milk (flour, baking powder and salt sifted 3 times) a little at a time.
Add vanilla flavoring. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: green stuff(dessert)
directions: Mix flour, soft butter and 1/2 cup of the chopped walnuts. Grease oblong pan and spread with mixture.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°, then cool.

title: belly bombers
directions: Combine ingredients together and spread onto sliced sourdough rounds.
Broil in the oven until bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: jalapeno pepper rice casserole
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in oleo; add salt.
Add rice, consomme and water to sauteed vegetables.
Pour in casserole. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: dill pickles
directions: Heat to boiling.
Pack into sterilized jars with a sprig of dill and cukes.
Pour in brine and seal at once.

title: cherry cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Beat softened cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Line cupcake pan with cupcake cups (papers) and put 1 vanilla wafer in each.
Fill 2/3 up with the mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with cherry pie filling and chill.

title: orange almond cake
directions: Grease and sprinkle with sugar a round layer pan 9 x 1 1/2 inches.
Heat oven to 350°F.
In a mixing bowl beat all ingredients together, except 2 tablespoons sugar, almonds and liquor.
Beat on high speed until mixture is creamy.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean or around 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar and drizzle with liquor.
Cool 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and toss gently. Refrigerate to blend flavors.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Brown beef; add onions and celery and cook until soft.
Add all ingredients in casserole and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 375°.
Uncover and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: scotch salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender; drain and cover with cold water. Drain again, well; add bananas, apples and pineapple.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage, stems, onion and parsley.
Add butter, bread crumbs, egg, water, salt, garlic powder and poultry seasoning. Stuff mushrooms and place on buttered cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Combine cheese and bacon in a bowl.

In a large salad bowl, alternate spinach, cheese mixture, mushrooms, onions and peas. Mix mayonnaise and yogurt; pour or spread over top of salad. Last, sprinkle a little more grated cheese over the top.
Make day before and store, covered, in refrigerator.
Enjoy!

title: hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese with milk and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Put in an 8-inch ovenproof dish and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
May be topped with sliced toasted almonds.
Serve with crackers or Melba rounds.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Blend first seven ingredients. Whisk in olive oil and pepper. Marinate chicken at least one hour. Grill or broil over medium heat until cooked through.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Put remaining ingredients in blender.
Cover and process mix until smooth.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Add raisins and mix well.
Pour into small tube pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pa pa's dog bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and egg.
Pour into well oiled 10 inch heavy skillet (iron skillet) which has been heated. Cook in preheated 500° oven until golden
brown.

title: southern prune cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in 325° oven for 35 minutes. Delicious with cream cheese frosting.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs and add butter and vanilla.
Mix flour and sugar. Add to egg; mix and then add chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm topped with ice cream.

title: chocolate cherry upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread pie filling evenly over the bottom of prepared pan.
In a large bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine liquids. Add to flour mixture all at once; stir just to moisten.
Pour batter evenly over cherry pie filling. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool 10 minutes in pan; invert and cool.

title: raspberry walnut shortbread
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Combine flour and sugar, cut in butter until mixture is like fine meal.
Press over the bottom of lightly greased 7 x 11 inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes, or just until edges become slightly browned.
Remove from oven and let cool slightly.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit in bowl.
Toss with yogurt to coat all fruit. Cover and chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon party ball
directions: Drain and flake salmon, removing any skin and bones.
Combine salmon, cream cheese, lemon juice, salt and liquid smoke; mix well.
Chill several hours.
Combine pecans and parsley.
Shape salmon mixture in a ball.
Roll in nut mixture; chill well.
Serve with crackers.

title: fruit pie
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries.
Add to this juice enough water to equal 1 cup.
Add sugar and cornstarch, vanilla and food coloring.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in fruit and nuts. Pour into 2 cooked pie shells.
Cover with whipped cream and chill.
By using Equal, cherries packed in water and pineapple packed in its own juice, this dessert is good for diabetics.

title: soft raisin cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water for 5 minutes. Strain and save 1/4 cup of liquid. Cool raisins. Blend shortening, spices, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture and mix well. Add reserved liquid from raisins and then raisins. Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on to cookie sheets 2 inches apart. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar, Clear Jell and butter until thick.
Add strawberry jello and red food color.
Fill baked pie shell with strawberries.
Pour glaze over berries.
Refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream if desired.

title: graham cracker roll
directions: Roll 16 graham crackers and mix with dates, marshmallows, pecans and whipped cream.
Form into a roll, then roll in the crumbs of 4 remaining graham crackers.
Chill, slice and serve with whipped cream and a cherry on top.
This freezes well.

title: banana pie
directions: Heat milk over medium heat.
Meanwhile, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir into milk until mixture is smooth and comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in half the egg yolks; pour mixture into remaining egg yolks and mix well.
Return to heat and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell filled with sliced bananas. Chill until firm.
Spread with Banana Pie Topping.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix all together and then add pint of Dream Whip.
Pour into baked pie shell and refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: apple enchilada dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spoon fruit evenly onto all tortillas, sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up tortillas and place seam side down on lightly greased 8x8 baking pan.
Bring butter, sugars and water to boil in a med. saucepan.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly for 3 min.
Pour sauce evenly over tortillas; sprinkle with extra cinnamon on top if desired.
Bake in preheated oven for 20 min.
Makes 6 large tortillas; may be cut in half to serve 12.

title: bacon-cheese biscuits
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal; set aside.
Combine buttermilk and soda, stirring until soda dissolves.
Add mixture to bacon, cheese and flour mixture, stirring until all ingredients are moistened.
Turn out dough onto lightly floured surface and knead slightly 4 to 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat
oven to 425°.	Mix ingredients in order given. Pour into
pie
shell.
Bake
15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool completely. Garnish with whipped topping if desired.

title: dark moist cake
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add milk, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Beat well and add the 1 cup of hot coffee.
Beat well. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar and mayonnaise and stir in cabbage.

title: pipikaula
directions: In a large bowl combine steak and all other ingredients except honey.
Marinate for 48 hours in refrigerator, turning about 4 times.

title: layered taco appetizer
directions: Mix avocado dip with sour cream, then layer in order listed. Serve with corn chips.

title: peanut butter-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour and baking soda.
Beat peanut butter, butter, sugars and vanilla with electric mixer until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
With mixer on low speed, gradually beat in flour mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute before removing to rack to cool completely.
Store tightly covered.

title: raspberry holiday mold
directions: Drain pineapple chunks and raspberries, reserving liquid; set liquid aside.
Press raspberries through a sieve or food mill.
Set the puree aside, and discard seeds.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate about 8 hours before serving.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Cook cranberries in red pop until soft.
Remove from heat and dissolve gelatin in cranberry mix.
Add pineapple.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix pudding, pineapple and juice well.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: sauerbraten steak
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch squares.
Brown meat.
After cooking completely, remove from skillet.
Add gravy mix and 2 c.
water. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in next 6 ingredients, plus salt and pepper.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Add meat. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaf before serving over hot noodles.

title: raspberry jello mold
directions: Mix jello according to package directions minus 1 cup water. Refrigerate until it starts to take shape.
Beat with mixer until jello turns fluffy.
(It will turn a shade lighter in color.) Beat in Cool Whip.
Drain oranges and pineapple.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Pour into desired serving dish.
Garnish.

title: the gingerbread men
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, molasses, egg and vinegar.
Mix well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and spices and add to molasses mixture.
Shape dough into a ball and knead until smooth.
Chill overnight.
Divide dough.
Roll to 1/4 inch thick on floured surface.
Cut with 4 inch gingerbread cutter and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Makes about 12 gingerbread men.

title: biscuits
directions: Stir thoroughly the first 5 ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in center; add milk all at once.
Stir just until dough clings together.
Knead gently on lightly floured surface, 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll or pat to 1/2-inch thickness. Dip 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter in flour; cut dough straight down.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.
Yields 12 biscuits.

title: cherry gelatin salad
directions: In a saucepan, heat the Jell-O and crushed pineapple until dissolved.
Let cool.
In a bowl, add the buttermilk, Cool Whip, pecans and Jell-O and pineapple mixture.
Mix well.
Let chill until set.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Rinse, shell and devein shrimp.
Prepare seafood stock from shrimp shells and heads.
Heat 1/4 cup margarine over high heat in a 5-quart pan.
Add 1 cup onions.
Cook, stirring frequently, for approximately 3 minutes or until caramelized.
Add remaining onions, celery, green pepper and 4 tablespoons margarine.
Cook until tender.
Add garlic, bay leaf, salt, pepper, hot sauce and 1/2 of stock.
Cook on medium heat for 5 minutes to blend and finish veggies, stirring often.
Add tomatoes; simmer on low for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining tomato sauce, stock and sugar.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook until pink and plump, approximately 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve 1 cup sauce with 1/2 cup rice.
Serves 10.

title: cheese and vegetable soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook all of the vegetables in 4 tablespoons of liquid Butter Buds.
Cover; stir occasionally.
Cook about 20 to 30 minutes on low heat.
Add more liquid Butter Buds if needed.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken broth to vegetable mixture.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in cheese.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until cheese is melted. Gradually add milk.
Season with lite salt and pepper.
Bring to almost boiling, but do not boil.
Sprinkle with parsley and seasoned croutons.
Serves 8.

title: peach ambrosia
directions: In a large bowl, gently mix pineapple, marshmallows, grapes, orange segments and 3/4 cup of the coconut.
Stir in 1/2 cup of the sour cream.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours or up to 24 hours.

title: smothered steak
directions: Roll steak pieces in flour.
Brown steak in skillet.
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour over browned steak.
Let simmer for 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
When steak is done, you also have your gravy for potatoes.

title: hedge hogs
directions: Melt butter and add sugar, egg, nuts and dates.
Cook 6 minutes, stirring slowly with a wooden spoon.
Add Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Let cool.
Shape into fingers and roll with coconut.

title: german sausage and kraut
directions: Dice up sausage, potatoes and onion and place in nonstick pan. On medium heat, cook with a cover until sausage is done and potatoes are soft (approximately 25 to 30 minutes).
Add sauerkraut.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes on low heat.
Dish out onto plate and drizzle syrup across the top.

title: hot citrus tea
directions: Bring 2 cups water and cloves to a boil.
Remove from heat and let stand 2 hours.
Steep tea bags in 1 1/2 quarts water for 5 minutes.
Remove bags.
Strain clove mixture and add to tea.
Add sugar and fruit mixtures, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cook over low heat until heated.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook butter, sugar and water to 250°, using candy thermometer. Add sliced almonds; continue to cook to 300°.
Remove from heat. Add salt and vanilla.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 package of chocolate chips over mixture; let melt 5 to 10 minutes.
Smooth to coat.
Add nuts.
Refrigerate at least 1/2 hour.
Loosen edges and turn entire mixture over.
Melt other package of chocolate chips and spread with nuts as other side.
Chill well.
Crack into small servings.

title: delicious pork
directions: Cut pork into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Flatten slightly into a rounded shape.
Brown pork in butter; about 5 minutes per side. Season with salt and pepper and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a well-greased pan.
Pour off fat.
Turn oven up to 500°.
Mix cheese, mustard and 2 tablespoons whipping cream in bowl.
Spread mixture over pork and bake at 500° for 3 to 5 minutes or until topping bubbles.
Remove pork from pan and keep warm.
In the pan, the pork was cooked in, mix apple juice and 3 1/2 tablespoons of whipping cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly and scraping the bottom and sides of the pan.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, until sauce is slightly thickened.
Pour over pork and sprinkle with parsley.

title: pineapple-almond torte
directions: *This is not a misprint, nearly 1 full cup will be needed for this recipe.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients except for stuffing.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with stuffing and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: merry munchies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Combine butter, brown sugar, egg and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.

title: hearty cabbage stew
directions: Saute ground round in 8-quart pot with onion; toss in shredded cabbage, cook until tender, adding water as needed.
Add spices and stir, to meat and cabbage.
Dice carrots, add to pot. Add 2 cups water, cover with lid; cook until tender.
Add green beans, broccoli and corn; cook until tender.
Add diced tomatoes and tomato sauce and 1 cup water and crowder peas.
Stir and cook for 1 to 2 hours on low-medium.
Add more water and spices as needed.
Serves about 12.
Serve with corn bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix melted margarine and corn bread dressing mix together. Combine sour cream, chicken soup and milk.
Place 1/2 of corn bread mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with chopped chicken.
Pour sour cream mixture over chicken.
Top with rest of corn bread mixture.
Pour chicken broth over all.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
tags: Stove Top corn bread dressing mix

title: italian sausage and potato pie
directions: Cut sausage into large links. Pierce several times.
Place in skillet with water to cover. Boil until water evaporates.
Brown sausages in remaining fat, then remove to a pan and cut into 1/4-inch rounds.
Lightly oil a 10-inch pie pan. Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine oil and spices.
Toss with potatoes. Make a layer of potatoes, then sausage and then Ricotta. Repeat and finish with potatoes. Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake.

title: steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
In large skillet (ovenproof if desired) brown meat in oil, using high heat.
Add onions.
Saute until tender. Add mushrooms.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour or cover and bake at 350°.
Serve over bed of fluffy rice. Makes 6 servings.
Good reheated!

title: lasagne
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine ground beef, sausage and onion. Microwave at High for 5 to 6 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, stirring 2 times; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Stir to blend and break apart tomatoes.
Set aside.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken in water with broth and then debone it.
Set aside 2 1/2 cups of broth.
Add cream of mushroom soup to the 2 1/2 cups of broth.
Add Velveeta, flour and Lipton soup mix.
Cook all together over low heat until Velveeta is melted.
Cook small package of spaghetti in remaining broth.
Add the Velveeta mix to spaghetti and put in large casserole dish.
Heat in oven until hot all the way through.
Serve.
This can be fixed ahead of time and then heated when ready to serve.

title: mexican ugly dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and chill in refrigerator 1 to 2 hours.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook the corn bread; let cool.
Crumble into a bowl then add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: my best biscuits
directions: Mix biscuit mix, sour cream and club soda.
Pat out on floured wax paper until dough is not sticky.
Cut out biscuits and place them on greased pan.
Brush half the melted margarine on top of biscuits before baking and the rest after baking.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until brown.

title: hot green beans
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Fry 6 pieces of bacon and remove from skillet.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Combine all in covered casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour.
When done, crumble bacon on top.

title: beef and rice skillet
directions: Cook ground beef and green pepper in skillet.
Stir in rice and water, contents of gravy mix, onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 5 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Yields about 4 servings.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Combine ice cream, peanut butter, 1/4 cup peanuts and vanilla in a large bowl and mix well.
Turn into crust and sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Freeze.
Serve with hot fudge and whipped topping, if desired.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand for 20 minutes.
Mix butter and sugar; add eggs, soda, salt and flour.
Mix in oats, pour into 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Place in baking dish. Crumble crackers in melted margarine and sprinkle on top.
Bake about 30 minutes.

title: caramel nuts
directions: Caramelize 1 cup sugar
in
a
small
heavy pan.
While cooking, mix 3 cups sugar, cream
and
salt
in
a larger pan; when mixture comes to a boil, add caramelized sugar to mixture and cook until it comes to
a
soft
ball
(when
dropped
in water). Cool and beat; when it
holds,
dip end of nut in and drop on waxed paper.
If it gets too hard, add a little cream. You can also use this for cake icing.

title: corn bread picante
directions: Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: dr. pepper marinade for  brisket(miscellaneous)
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate overnight.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes about 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Beat egg and milk in bowl; combine flour and cornmeal.
Dip each slice individually in milk and egg mixture and then in flour and meal mixture.
Have shortening about 1/2-inch deep in heavy skillet.
When shortening is hot, place tomatoes in and fry until brown on both sides.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and bananas.
Then add the rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in a 10 x 14-inch pan.

title: apricot fritters
directions: Dry apricot halves on paper toweling until as dry as possible. Beat egg with milk; stir in the melted shortening.
Combine the flour, granulated sugar, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture and stir just until mixed.
Dip apricots in batter.
Fry, a few at a time, in deep shortening, heated to 365° until fritters are brown, about 4 minutes, turning once.
Do not use the frying basket.
Drain on paper toweling.
Roll in confectioners sugar. Serve warm.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Split shrimp and season with salt, red pepper and black pepper.
Melt margarine or oil and add onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook slowly in uncovered heavy pot until onion is wilted.
Add seasoned shrimp and let simmer, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and add to mixture.
Cook another 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: pressed chicken loaf
directions: Remove chicken from bones. Grind in food processor. Mix all ingredients together. Add more or less broth as needed.
Place in any desired mold or rectangular pan. Layer sliced eggs as you press loaf in mold. Leave a few for the top as garnish. Chill several hours.

title: cheese fingers
directions: Mix with hands the cake mix, 1 egg and margarine and press into a 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Mix together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 2 eggs.
Beat with a mixer and pour on top of pressed batter.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: strawberry cream squares
directions: Stir jello into boiling water until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries.
Stir until thawed.
Add well drained crushed pineapple and finely diced bananas.

title: frosty strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine strawberries, egg whites and sugar.
Beat at highest speed until thick and creamy.
Beat whip cream and fold in gently. Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Freeze 4 or 5 hours.
Serve frozen.

title: drop egg soup
directions: In a saucepan, combine the chicken broth, the celery with leaves, green onion, bottled hot sauce and the ginger.
Bring mixture to boiling.
Slowly pour the beaten egg into the soup. Stir once, gently, so the egg forms thin shreds.
Remove from heat.
Serve the soup immediately.
Serves 2.

title: liver sausage pate'
directions: Mix together.
Press into a greased mold pan.
Place in the freezer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: anita's spuds
directions: Combine everything except cheese and microwave until potatoes are done.
Remove from microwave and top with cheese.
Return to microwave and cook only until the cheese melts.

title: salmon puffs
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Spray the vegetable oil over the baking sheet 3 times to coat.
Put the cornmeal, thyme and basil on a large plate and mix well.
Sprinkle 1/8 teaspoon of the garlic powder, 1/8 teaspoon of the lemon pepper and 1 teaspoon of the blackening seasoning on each of the catfish fillets.
Coat the fillets thoroughly with the cornmeal mixture and transfer them to the prepared baking sheet.
Dust each fillet with 1/8 teaspoon of the paprika.
Coat the catfish lightly with the cooking spray. Place the baking sheet on the bottom shelf of the oven.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Reduce the heat to 350° and bake for about 5 minutes more, until the crust is golden and the fish flakes easily.

title: caf swiss mocha
directions: Process in blender on liquefies until well blended. Store in airtight container.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in oblong glass baking dish and rest of ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: doritos chicken casserole
directions: Blend Ro-Tel, soups and milk.
Layer chicken, Doritos, chicken and Doritos.
Pour blended mixture over that and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients and add plain flour to make stiff enough to handle. Let rise until double in size.
Press down and roll out.
Place on pan which has been warmed and buttered.
Let rise
again. Bake in a preheated oven at 375°.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls, using about 2 teaspoons of the mixture for each ball.
Store in covered container for several days before serving.
Roll the candies in more sifted confectioners sugar or coconut.
Makes about 50.

title: v 8 aspic
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Add all other ingredients. Refrigerate. Serves 6.

title: cheese ball with shrimp sauce
directions: Mix and pour over 8 ounces of cream cheese.

title: lemon-pepper steak cutlets
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Place steak between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Cut into 4 equal pieces.

title: white christmas
directions: Put all ingredients except almond bark in paper bag.
Shake and pour into cookie sheets.
Melt almond bark in double boiler and pour small amount over cereal mix.
Sir.
Add more cereal, then almond bark until used up.
When dried use spatula.
Separate into pieces and place in closed container.

title: icebox pickles
directions: *Soak pickles overnight, before slicing.

title: sour cream crescent rolls
directions: Scald sour cream.
Stir in sugar, salt and melted butter. Cool until lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large bowl. Sprinkle in yeast and stir.
Add lukewarm sour cream mixture, eggs and flour.
Mix until well blended.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
(This is very important.)
Next day, turn out dough onto a lightly floured board.
Divide into 4 parts.
Roll each part into a 10-inch circle.
Cut each circle into 12 wedge-shaped pieces.
Roll each piece up from wide end and place on greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until browned.
If desired, brush with butter when removed from oven.

title: stephen's baked beans
directions: Allow navy beans to soak in water overnight.
Add remaining ingredients; cook on high in crock-pot for 5 to 6 hours.

title: monica's margaritas
directions: Blend ice with Bacardi Margarita mix and add your rum or tequila to your taste.
Wet top rim of cocktail glasses with lime and dip into salt.
Now pour Margarita into glass.
Decorate rim with limes or cherries.
For non-alcoholic drink, do not add the rum or tequila.

title: cheesy spinach
directions: Cook spinach until thawed.
Drain.
Add cheese and melt in microwave until all bubbly.
Yum!

title: real buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat egg until light, add buttermilk; mix well.
Combine with dry ingredients with a few swift strokes.
Beat in oil.
Pour batter for individual pancakes on hot skillet.
Makes ten 4-inch pancakes.

title: layered lemon dessert
directions: Melt oleo; add flour and nuts.
Put on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for about 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: After you have chicken in bottom of pan, mix together celery and chicken soup and broth.
Pour this over the chicken.
Mix together flour, milk, melted butter and baking powder.
Pour over the top of soups and chicken.
You may add mixed vegetables to the soups and broth, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour, or until done.

title: ham and swiss cheese rolls
directions: Cut rolls through middle.
Put spread on each half.
Put ham and cheese on rolls.
Can be frozen.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread the bean dip on a platter.
Next layer the sour cream on top of the bean dip.
Sprinkle the chilies, tomatoes and olives over the sour cream.
Top with the Cheddar cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: blueberry cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
Rinse blueberries from mix with cold water and drain.
Place muffin mix in medium bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender or two knives. Stir in pecans.
Press into bottom of pan.
Bake for 15 minutes or until set.
Combine cream cheese and sugar in medium bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Beat well. Spread over baked crust.
Sprinkle with blueberries.
Sprinkle topping packet from mix over blueberries.
Return to oven.
Bake for an additional 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Cut into bars.
Makes about 16 bars.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Put ingredients into mixing bowl in order given, measuring flour after sifting once.
Don't stir until water is added.
Beat 3 minutes.
Bake at 350°.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: french bread
directions: Add butter to hot water and set aside until it melts.
Put 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl; stir this well.
Add water and butter; mix well with mixer.
Stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead for 5 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse and drain shrimp.
Mix all ingredients on mixer and blend well.
Keep covered in refrigerator.
Keeps for 3 weeks.

title: boiled fruit cake
directions: Bring first 8 ingredients to a boil in a large saucepan.
Cook 5 minutes and cool.
Stir in flour and soda (which has been dissolved in very small amount of water).
Add nuts and fruit in amounts to your liking (up to 2 cups each).
More raisins may also be added.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
This makes a very large cake, baked in a tube pan or can be baked in about 3 loaf pans.
Be sure to grease and flour pans well.

title: creamy cabbage-and-apple slaw
directions: In large salad bowl, combine cabbage, onion and pepper strips. Toss apple and raisins with lemon juice; add to cabbage.
In small bowl combine mayonnaise, sour cream, honey, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over cabbage.
Toss until evenly coated.
Cover slaw with plastic film and refrigerate until serving time.
Stir with fork just before serving.
Garnish with pepper rings, if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours. If too thick, add a small amount of the fruit juices.

title: oat crunch
directions: Grease bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Prepare brownie mix. Spoon into prepared pan.

title: easy brownie icing
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips, stirring until melted, then ice brownies.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan; lightly dust with flour.
Cream together the butter and 2 cups of the sugar.
Add eggs, blending well.
Then add the sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold the dry ingredients into the creamed mixture and beat.
Do not overbeat, just blend.
In separate bowl, mix remaining sugar, pecans and cinnamon.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Butter 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Line 24 graham crackers on pan.
Melt and boil 3 minutes on medium heat.
Stir constantly. Add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Pour over crackers and bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Cool and cut.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and margarine together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in refrigerator and chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped walnuts.
Place a cherry on top, if desired.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Boil soy sauce and sherry, then stir in sugar and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring lightly.
Add garlic, pepper and oil.
Set aside; cool before using.
Marinate chicken breast for 3 hours (more for a stronger taste).
Discard any used marinade.
Can be used with pork, beef, fish or vegetables.
Any unused marinade will keep indefinitely.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Brink to boil and boil 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 c. peanut butter and 3 cups uncooked rolled oats.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.
Cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Brown onions and celery in butter.
Add tomato soup to the onions, then beat egg into the mixture.
Add bread crumbs, seasoning and onion mixture to the meat.
Work well with hands until all ingredients are thoroughly blended.

title: sour cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Remove from blender and serve or use in recipes that need sour cream.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together with mixer.
Bake in three greased and floured (I use Pam, no flour) coffee cans at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool in cans for 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack to cool completely.
Return to can; trim top.
Put on lid for storage or freezing.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine mayo, sour cream, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add crab meat.
Add and mix thoroughly the sherry, lemon juice and onion.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Bake in pizza pan at 350° for 10 minutes or until browned.
Mix next four ingredients; spread over cooled crust.
Next spread strawberry glaze over filling; place sliced strawberries on top.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add melted butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Smash down with bottom glass dipped in flour.
Brush with egg whites.
Decorate if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves several dozen.

title: hardtack(knekke brod)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk. Roll out thinly.
Cut in diamond-shaped pieces.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat
together
margarine
and
sugars.
Add
eggs
and vanilla.
Combine
thoroughly.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt to butter mixture.
Add rolled oats, chocolate chips, raisins
and nuts.
Mix thoroughly after each addition. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix flour and meal together, then baking powder, sugar, milk, salt and eggs.
Beat well.
Grease pan and cook until brown.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix, butter and hot water; put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix everything but milk and eggs.
Put on top of stuffing mix.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over all and refrigerate overnight. Set out 2 hours before cooking.
Top with can of cream of mushroom soup and 8 ounces cream cheese.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.

title: orange cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Put whites in large mixer bowl until at room temperature.
On waxed paper, sift flour.
Fill cups to over full, then smooth off with spatula.
Sift flour again with salt.
With mixer at medium speed, beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Set aside.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine vegetables, tossing.
Combine remaining ingredients. Chill overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter in a large mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Gradually add whipped topping and confectioners sugar and continue beating until smooth.
Spoon filling into pie crusts and freeze for at least 8 hours.
May garnish with shaved chocolate and/or roasted peanuts.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Save the juice from pineapple.
Pour the pineapple over the bananas (so they won't turn dark).
Melt jello and marshmallows in water; add cold water and chill.
Add fruit.
Chill until set.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Peel shrimp, remove vein and wash.
Cut large shrimp in half. Cook onion, green pepper and garlic in butter until thick.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add tomatoes.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp and simmer about 20 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Mix milk, cornstarch and Equal in a small saucepan; heat to boiling.
Boil, stirring constantly, 1 minute.
Mix about half the milk mixture into eggs; mix egg mixture into milk in saucepan. Cook over low heat until slightly thickened, 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and cinnamon.
Cool to room temperature; refrigerate until chilled, or until serving time.

title: remarkable fudge(microwavable)
directions: In 2-quart bowl, place butter.
Cook at High for 45 seconds until melted.
Stir in sugar, milk and salt.
Cook at High for 3 1/2 minutes until the mixture comes to a full boil, stirring once. Mix well; cook at Medium or Cook Power 5 (50%) for 5 minutes.
Add the Marshmallow Creme and chocolate, peanut butter or butterscotch pieces, stirring until melted and smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into buttered, foil-lined 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cool; chill to firm.
Lift candy from foil and remove foil.
Cut into squares to serve.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: grandpa's shredded wheat
directions: Put Shredded Wheat squares in a cake pan.
Put about 2 pats of butter on each square.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Put in broiler for about 5 minutes.
Carefully put into a cereal bowl and add milk.

title: biscuits
directions: Blend flour, sugar and Crisco.
Mix in buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Roll out on lightly floured board. Cut.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: little pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients with mixer.
Put shortening on griddle. Serve rolled with jelly and confectioners sugar.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix and pour in pie shell and bake until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in casserole dish (I use a deep oval dish).
Pour 1/2 of the soup mixture over the chicken.
Prepare stuffing as the box tells you, then put rest of soup mixture in with it and pour it over the first half.
Bake in oven until brown on top, approximately 1/2 to 1 hour.
Serve with a couple of vegetables or with a green vegetable and mashed potatoes.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Mix fruits together in large glass bowl.
Cover with white grape juice mixed with orange extract.
Serve chilled.
Easy, colorful and delicious.

title: colonial cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla until very light and fluffy. Add flour gradually, mixing until well blended.
Chill dough in freezer for 30 minutes.
Roll out a third of the dough at a time. Keep remaining dough chilled.
On a lightly floured board, gently roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut out with cookie cutter. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool for a few minutes before removing from pan.

title: herb baked chicken
directions: Spray a 2-quart oblong baking dish with vegetable cooking spray; arrange chicken, bone side down, in dish.
Sprinkle with thyme and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of water for 5 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup of the water for sauce.
Combine onion with juice, horseradish, mayonnaise, lemon pepper and reserved water. Put carrots in a 2-quart buttered casserole.
Cover with sauce. Top with a mixture of cheese and bread crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese torte
directions: Combine crust ingredients and pat into bottom of a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: leftover hamburger patty casserole
directions: Lightly grease casserole dish.
Crumble chips in bottom of dish.
Crumble hamburger over chips.
Cover with tomatoes, layer again with chips and hamburger.
Top with cheese.
Heat in microwave for 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 5.

title: refrigerator ice cream
directions: Beat the eggs. Add sugar and continue beating.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Keep canned milk in refrigerator until well chilled.
Best if kept there overnight.
Whip milk until thick, then fold into beaten eggs and beat some more. Stir in pineapple and pour into refrigerator trays.
When it begins to freeze, remove and stir well. Return to freezer until ready to serve. This makes 8 servings.
You may substitute any fruit or keep this plain vanilla.

title: crab won tons
directions: Mix cream cheese, crab, onions and sesame oil.
Put scant teaspoon of mixture in a won ton skin and wrap according to directions on won ton package.
You may want to use a touch of the crab mixture to seal edges of won tons.
Deep fry 2 or 3 at a time just until golden brown (just a few seconds).
Serve with Chinese mustard and soy sauce for dipping.

title: hamburger salami
directions: Knead mixture with plastic gloves over hands.
Knead 5 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Knead again 5 minutes. Refrigerate 24 hours again.
Repeat this every 2 hours for 4 days. On 4th day, shape it into sausage like rolls, about 4-inches in diameter and about 12-inches long.
Put these on a wire rack over a roasting pan.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours, turning rolls a quarter turn every 30 minutes.
Cool and then refrigerate to use within a week.
Freeze them to be used within 3 months.

title: wacky cake
directions: Cake is mixed right in baking pan.

title: nice punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, but the ginger ale.
Chill about 45 minutes.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and chunk ice.

title: roll out sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, combine butter and sugar; cream together, then beat in egg and vanilla.
Next, add baking powder and flour, one cup at a time.
Roll out and cut.

title: dot's chicken
directions: Place flat chicken breasts in large pan.
Place 1 slice of Swiss cheese on each breast.
Mix 1/4 cup cooking sherry and 1 can cream of chicken soup.
Pour mixture over chicken and cheese. Sprinkle 1 cup of dry Stove Top stuffing on top.
Then drizzle 1/4 cup of melted margarine or butter over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: family bean bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In ungreased 3-quart baking dish, combine hot dogs, beans, ketchup and mustard; mix well.
In medium bowl, lightly beat egg.
Add milk and oil.
Stir in corn meal; mix well. Spoon batter over hot dog mixture.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: refrigerator spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add all other ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Place in airtight covered container and store in refrigerator.
As needed, spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° about 20 minutes.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Stir in corn syrup, vanilla and oatmeal.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Melt chocolate bits and peanut butter over low heat.
Spread over oatmeal mixture.
Makes 20 (2-inch) bars.

title: walnut bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Stir in oil, walnuts and milk.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serve hot or cold.

title: lemon ice
directions: Squeeze juice from fruit.
Measure water and sugar into saucepan. Stir well.
Heat mixture over medium heat until boiling. Boil 10 minutes.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Pour juice through strainer to mixing bowl.
Pour into plastic container; freeze until hard.
Scrape shavings into scoop size servings and serve.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put the apples and water in baking dish.
Mix together the remaining ingredients to make crumbs; sprinkle on top of apples. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In heavy pan, mix sugar, syrup and water.
Cook to 250°.
Add nuts.
Cook and stir to 310°.
Add butter, salt and soda, stirring constantly.
Have ready spray Pam on clean counter top and rub butter over top of Pam.
Pour candy on top of counter.
Butter hands.
Pull and stretch candy until thickness desired.

title: fiesta corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Crumble Ramen noodles into a large baking sheet (with rim on). Add almonds and bake until lightly brown.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Mix gelatin and water.
Set aside.
Heat soup to boiling.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted.
Add gelatine mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill in a 1 1/2-quart mold.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli with swiss
directions: Put broccoli in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and put on top of broccoli.
Broil until bubbly and light brown.
Other frozen vegetables may be used in place of broccoli.

title: zucchini pineapple loaf
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla until thick and foamy. With a spoon, stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts.
Stir gently into zucchini mixture.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, well greased and floured.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: chili
directions: Brown and drain first 3 ingredients.
Combine the rest of the ingredients with hamburg and simmer for 4 hours.

title: coconut tarts
directions: Combine ingredients, except jam.
Place 1 teaspoon of jam in each tart shell.
Cover with 1 teaspoon of coconut mixture.
Bake in moderate oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen tarts.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Cream the butter and cheese. Beat until smooth. Combine flour and salt. Add 1/2 at a time to cheese mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Shape in a ball.

Wrap in wax paper and chill until pastry will roll and handle easily. Roll and cut in 2-inch circles. Bake in 2-inch muffin cup pans in very hot oven (450°) about 12 minutes or until light brown. Cool before filling.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef over medium-high heat; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes.
Serve, if desired, over toasted hamburger rolls.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Make at least 4 hours ahead.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion, broccoli, salt and pepper together.
Pour in casserole dish.
Melt butter.
Mix stuffing and cheese with butter and spread over top.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: invisible banana french toast
directions: Blend eggs, banana and cinnamon in blender until smooth.
Pour into a shallow dish.
Dip both sides of bread in mixture.
Fry in a lightly greased skillet until browned on both sides.
Serve warm with honey or powdered sugar.

title: spicy turkey stir-fry
directions: In nonstick skillet, saute garlic and vegetables in olive oil. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes, or until done.
Serve over rice with crispy chow mein noodles. Serves 2.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cut sausage into 1/4-inch pieces.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper to oil in a heavy saucepan; saute.
Drain.
Add consomme and rice.
Place ingredients in a greased 4-quart shallow baking dish. Pour in hot water and stir well.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove cover.
Add almonds and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Combine together in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread cheese on top.
Heat in oven until melted. Serve hot.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Beat together on medium speed the brown sugar, white sugar and butter or shortening. Add the eggs. Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and soda and add 1/4 of the flour mixture to the first mixture.
Alternate flour mixture with the applesauce until all ingredients are added. Add the vanilla, nuts and raisins. Bake at 350° until cake does not leave imprint when touched.

title: non-baked chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix
the first 5 ingredients;
cook, stirring constantly.
Let boil 5 minutes again.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; stir in the oatmeal.
Drop onto wax paper by teaspoon.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Microwave about 5 minutes on High.
Add peanuts. Microwave 2 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave 2 minutes more.
Stir in baking soda, butter and vanilla.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: spinach enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan, whisk together broth, tomato paste and chili powder.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. In a bowl,
combine spinach, onions, sour cream and cottage cheese; stir in 1 cup shredded cheese.
Spoon 1/2 cup sauce into a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Dip tortillas into remaining sauce.
Spoon 1/4 cup spinach mixture down the center of each tortilla.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in baking dish.
Top with remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put rice in and set aside. Melt margarine; add onion, soup, water, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Cook until cheese melts.
Put broccoli on top of rice.
Pour on sauce; mix well.
Bake in 350° oven 1/2 hour or until bubbly, uncovered.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients. Chill. Serve with Melba toast or bread cubes.

title: cherry pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup finely chopped pecans.

In a large mixing bowl, beat the cheese, butter, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Combine flour and baking powder. Add to batter and mix well. Stir in the cherries and coarsely chopped pecans.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes and remove from pan.
Garnish and frost as desired.
Makes one 10-inch cake.

title: picante "taco" sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes for about 20 minutes.
Chop peppers, onions and garlic fine.
Mix with tomatoes and spices.
Cook for 45 minutes. Then add cornstarch mixed with a little water to mixture.
Put into hot clean jars and seal.
This is good with chips!

title: chicken pot pie(100 servings)
directions: *Canned chicken may be used.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put layers of potatoes in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour.
Dot with butter.
Repeat steps until potatoes are gone.
Add milk until it may be seen through top layer.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours in moderate oven at 350°, or until potatoes are tender.

title: curried vegetables with eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onions and saute until softened (3 to 5 minutes).
Stir in curry powder and cook, stirring, 1 minute.
Add mushrooms, peppers and squash and stir until the mushrooms are limp and exude their liquid.
Add tomatoes and mash with a wooden spoon. Stir in red pepper flakes and simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Stir in tomato paste and season with salt and pepper. (The recipe cane be prepared up to this point and stored covered in the refrigerator for up to 2 days.)
Reheat before continuing.

title: quick and easy salad
directions: Make dressing as follows:

title: pinwheel appetizers
directions: Mix cheese, olives, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Spread evenly on tortillas.
Roll tortillas tightly.
Chill 2 hours or more. Cut into 1-inch thick slices.
Discard ends.
Serve with spirals facing up.

title: kellogg's "k" squares
directions: Bring syrup and butter just to a boil.
Add the peanut butter; stir until blended.
Add cereal and mix.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Frost with chocolate chips melted in a double boiler.
Cool before cutting.

title: confetti cookies
directions: Cream thoroughly the sugar, Crisco, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients slowly.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie pan. Flatten with fork.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Rinse and drain shrimp.
Chop shrimp with green onions. Moisten with mayonnaise so that the mixture is spreadable.
Add lemon juice.
Let sit in the refrigerator at least 12 hours. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: jumbo chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Combine flour, baking soda and salt in bowl. Beat together the butter, peanut butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar in a large bowl until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Beat in the eggs and vanilla until blended. Stir in the flour mixture until blended and dough forms. Stir in the chocolate chunks or chocolate chips and chopped pecans. Using a 1/4-cup measure, drop dough by slightly rounded mounds onto large ungreased baking sheets, spacing the cookies about 2-inches apart. Bake in a 325° oven 15 to 17 minutes until golden brown around edges and lightly colored on top. Remove the baking sheets to a wire rack to cool for about 3 minutes. Remove the cookies with a metal spatula from the baking sheets to a wire rack and cool completely. Makes 24 cookies at 28 cents each. Prep: 20 minutes. Bake: at 325° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients as for pie crust and cut in shortening (I always used lard.)
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with large cookie cutter.
Sprinkle cookies with sugar, if desired.
Bake in 375° oven until edges start to brown.

title: special chicken dish(feeds 8 to 10)
directions: Place the chicken breasts in buttered oblong baking dish. Cover with small amount of butter. Cover with the cheese over butter, then the stuffing. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Cover with foil; uncover short time before serving.

title: amish wedding recipe
directions: Blend 1 cup of love and 1/2 cup of kindness.
Add alternately in small portions 1 cup of appreciation and 3 cups of pleasant companionship into which have been sifted 3 teaspoons of deserving praise.
Flavor with 1 teaspoon of carefully chosen advice. Lightly fold in 1 cup of cheerfulness to which has been added a pinch of sorrow.
Pour with tender care into small clean hearts and let bake until well matured.
Turn out on the surface of society. Humbly invoke God's blessing and it will serve all mankind.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding with 3 1/2 cups milk, fold in Cool Whip.
Crush Oreos; set aside.
In another bowl, cream oleo, cream cheese and sugar.
Add these ingredients to pudding mix; mix well.
Then in bottom of planter place foil to cover hole.
Put layer of crushed Oreos, layer of pudding mix etc., layer all the way to rim of planter, with Oreos on top.
When placing flowers in mix, put stems of flowers in straws.

title: sweet and sour smokies
directions: Put Smokies (along with any liquid from package) into a large skillet and brown lightly.
Originally they were not supposed to be browned, but I usually did by accident and they turned out okay, so I put that part in the recipe.
When good and hot, add your jelly and stir well.
You will need to get out all of the jelly lumps. Now you will add approximately 1/2 of the mustard.
Mix well.
At this point, it is very unattractive and you'll be tempted to deposit the whole mess down the garbage disposal, but I promise it will get better.
