You will need to heat over medium burner until thickened.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except can of onion rings, place in 350° oven and bake until casserole begins to bubble.
Remove from oven, place can of onion rings on top of casserole and place back into oven until brown.

title: tomato tart
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put tomato slices on paper towels.
Pat slices to remove excess moisture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. In a small skillet, heat oil; saute garlic and onion until softened.
Cool.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of the Parmesan cheese over crust.
Top with onion mixture and lay the tomato slices in a pretty pattern on top.

title: mounds cakes
directions: First Layer:
Make cake as directed on box.
Divide evenly between 2 greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Season meat with garlic powder, onion powder or Lawry's seasoning. Make into 4 patties. Tear 4 large pieces of tinfoil and put meat patties in each one.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Grind meat together twice.
Soak bread in cream about 5 minutes.
Cook onions in 1 tablespoon of butter until tender. Combine meats, crumb mixture, onion, egg, parsley and seasonings. Beat until fluffy, about 5 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Brown in 2 tablespoons butter and remove.
Make gravy.
Stir flour into drippings.
Add broth, water and coffee.
Heat and stir until thickened.
Return meat balls to gravy. Cover and cook slowly, about 30 minutes, basting occasionally.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen balls.

title: hawaiian pineapple cake
directions: Topping:
Combine coconut with 1/2 of the pineapple; set aside.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar, egg yolks and tapioca in top of double boiler. Cook over boiling water until tapioca is dissolved and rhubarb is tender.
Stir in butter.
Pour in baked pie shell. Beat until foamy the egg whites. Add sugar gradually. Beat to soft peak stage.
Put over pie and bake until meringue is brown.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt oleo and saute onion in it.
Add bouillon cubes, chicken broth, rice and spinach.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.

title: low-calorie strawberry nog
directions: Fill a 1-cup measure with ice.
Add water to fill cup.
Pour into blender.
Add strawberries, egg, dry milk, vanilla and sugar. Cover and blend at high speed until thick and creamy.
Pour into tall glass.
Garnish with peppermint leaves.
Serve cold.

title: lemon jello cabbage salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil the remaining ingredients, cool and pour over cabbage, other veggies and oil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep 2 to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: barbecue cups
directions: You will also need Pam spray.

title: old settler's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick mock chicken casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and rinse with hot water.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package instructions.
Place beef in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon stuffing over meat.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over stuffing. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats and butterscotch chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put ingredients all together and mix well.
Melt 1 stick of oleo and stir in enough croutons or cracker crumbs to cover top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: squash relish
directions: Soak first four ingredients in salt and water to cover for 1 1/2 hours.
Bring vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed to a boil.
Drain squash and add to vinegar mixture.
Stir until mixture boils.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Yields 4 pints.

title: billy's stuff
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat. Prepare shells and cheese as directed. Add Ranch Style beans and hamburger and stir. Best served with cornbread. Serves approximately 4 to 6.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles; set aside. Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Over a low heat, mix hamburger, cream cheese and mushroom soup.
Melt slowly. Add peas, if desired.
Mix with noodles.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger meat and meat loaf mix; shape into meat balls and brown.
Add a little water and simmer until done.
Mix grape jelly, chili sauce and crushed pineapple and combine with meat. Cook in crock-pot 3 to 4 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Cut up pecans before toasting.
Toast in glass dish in microwave until you can smell them, 4 to 5 minutes.
Taste them. May need a few more minutes.

title: mama's prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts, in large bowl.
Fold in nuts last by hand.
Place in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and butter together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Stir in food coloring and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt and cocoa to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing when cake is completely cool.

title: never fail pie meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and water until cooked clear.
Set aside; cool good.
Beat egg whites and salt until it stands in peaks, then add the above cornstarch mixture.
Beat again until well mixed, then add gradually the sugar.
Beat until very creamy, then add vanilla if you want.
Pile on hot or cold pie; bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Should be golden brown.

title: daube pork
directions: Wash meat in vinegar and water.
Put all ingredients in bowl and cover.
Allow to sit 45 minutes to 1 hour for seasoning to penetrate meat.
Remove seasoning.
In a pot, add cooking oil and brown the meat.
Add seasoning.
Brown 1/2 hour.
Add hot water and simmer until tender.
Do not dry out.
Simmer to a gravy.

title: basque potato soup
directions: Brown sausage with onions and drain. Combine all ingredients. Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: crunchy chocolate sauce
directions: In skillet, saute nuts in butter until golden.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Serve warm over ice cream (sauce will harden).
Store in the refrigerator.
This sauce can be reheated in microwave.

title: mexican rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, saute first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes. Add rice; cook 1 minute and stir often.
Add water, sauce, tomatoes and chilies.
Cover.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Let stand covered (off heat) 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pecan pesto
directions: Food process first 8 ingredients, adding them one at a time. Pour this mixture into a bowl and add the oil and Parmesan.
Mix well.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all together and store in container.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Let stand a few minutes before slicing.

title: rolled oats toll house cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars. Beat in eggs. Sift together flour, soda and add to creamed mixture. Stir in hot water, oats, chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350 for 8-10 minutes. Let sit for 1-2 minutes on sheets before lifting with spatula to racks to cool.
These freeze very well and are even great eaten right from the freezer!

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients: flour, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
Add milk to creamed mixture.
Then add dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls into hot canola oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning frequently.
Roll in powdered sugar or serve plain. Wonderful when hot, good when cold.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, pepper and onion together and lay in bottom of a casserole dish. Top with both the soups.
Top this with a layer of frozen Tater Tots and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Fry hamburg, onions, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Drain hamburg and noodles.
Mix in large bowl.
Then add soups, mushrooms and pizza sauce.
Mix well.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix sauce ingredients thoroughly. During the last 10 minutes of cooking time, brush chicken generously and frequently with sauce. Best if chicken is cooked on the grill.

title: all good pie
directions: Mix and put in uncooked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven until light brown.
Good for Christmas.

title: simply delicious pork
directions: Place tenderloins on aluminum foil.
Lightly salt and pepper. Pour salad dressing over tenderloins.
Seal foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cheese corn bread
directions: Blend milk and mustard and add beaten egg.
Combine corn muffin mix and Parmesan cheese.
Add milk mixture, stirring until just mixed.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a hot oven (400°) for 18 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese evenly over the top and bake 1 minute longer or until cheese is slightly melted.
Serve warm.
Serves 8 or 9.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
While stirring, cook for 3 to 5 minutes.
Set aside until cool, then eat shrimp and vegetables together.

title: angelic oysters
directions: Arrange the oysters in a baking pan.
Mix all ingredients except almonds together and blend until smooth.
Place a heaping teaspoonful of the butter mixture on each oyster.
Sprinkle with about 5 slices of almonds.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes or until almonds begin to brown.
Serves 4.

title: unbelievable lasagne
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, spread 1 cup sauce.
Arrange a layer of uncooked lasagne; top with some sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan and sauce.
Repeat, gently pressing lasagne into cheese mixture.
End with final layer of lasagne; pour remaining sauce over, making sure all lasagne pieces are covered.
Top with remaining cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, until lightly browned and bubbling.
Allow to stand 15 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve 6 to 8.

title: easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Season chicken with 1/2 teaspoon salt and paprika.
Place bacon strips on the bottom and sides of casserole dish.
Pour uncooked rice over the bacon.
Dilute soup with the 1/2 cup water and pour over rice.
Place the chicken on top and season again with a little salt and cayenne pepper.
Add oregano.
Sprinkle top with parsley.
Seal the top of the casserole with foil.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours without peeking!
If using chicken breasts, cook about 1 1/2 hours.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Add together soy sauce, sugar and mirin to make sauce for later.

title: ham barbecues
directions: Brown onions, green pepper and celery in margarine until tender (chop onions, green pepper and celery).
Add tomato soup, chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar.
Simmer until thick.
Add ham (chop up ham).
Simmer for about 1/2 hour.

title: buckeyes
directions: Soften and cream oleo with beater. Add peanut butter and cream again. Add sifted powdered sugar, a little at a time. (Toward the end you will have to mix with your hands.) Form into balls the size of a buckeye (walnut) and chill 2 hours.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture until blended.
Stir in nuts. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough onto greased baking sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: starlight mint surprise cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Blend into creamed mixture eggs, water and vanilla.
Beat well and then add flour.
Chill dough.
Put chocolate wafer candy (chocolate, mint or whatever) into 1 tablespoon chilled dough.
Cover wafer with dough.
(It's a surprise when you bite the cookie.) Place on cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Kids love these!

title: carrot cake
directions: Grate carrots or combine carrots, oil and eggs in blender and liquify.
In large bowl combine flour, sugar, soda, powder, salt, cinnamon, nuts and carrot mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in middle.
Let cool and remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost with chocolate frosting.

title: crispy crumb fried chicken
directions: Combine stuffing mix, salt, pepper & paprika on waxed paper. Moisten chicken with water & coat with crumbs.
Heat Crisco to 365° (in electric skillet or on medium high in large heavy skillet.
Fry chicken, turning once for even browning reduce heat to medium low. Cook chicken until tender.
Turn once for even browning.
Drain on paper towels. 4 servings.

title: rice caliente
directions: Crumble ground beef in lightly buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with rice and onions.
Combine tomatoes with green chilies, broth, salt and garlic powder in saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over meat mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir in sour cream and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven and bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 9.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Then pour over other ingredients after mixing them together.
Pour into two graham cracker crusts. Chill before serving.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into well-greased iron skillet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Wilt whole cabbage leaves in hot boiling water.
Cover balls of beef with cabbage leaf and secure with toothpicks.
In a slow cooker layer kraut, tomatoes and cabbage rolls until all are used. Cook on medium to high all day.
If you cook on the stove, you will have to add water periodically, but cook at least 6 hours. Will make about 10 rolls.
You can double recipe.

title: "diabetic" banana cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening, sugar replacement and cocoa thoroughly; add eggs and vanilla extract. Beat well.
Add mashed bananas alternately with dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: restaurant cheese soup
directions: In a heavy pan, cook potatoes, carrots, celery, onion and peppers in butter. Add broth and simmer for 30 minutes. Blend milk and flour and add to broth. Add cheese, parsley and chicken soup. Stir until cheese is melted and mixed together. Serve warm.

title: crab-stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Cut in half and scoop out potato, saving shells.
Put scooped out potato in bowl; mix with remaining ingredients with exception of bread crumbs and paprika.
Stir in crabmeat last and spoon mixture into potato shells.
Top with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini cupcakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar, oil, orange juice and almond extract.
Combine dry ingredients, add to egg mixture and mix well.
Add zucchini and mix well.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until cupcakes test done.
Cool 10 minutes before putting on wire rack.

title: "quickie 3 bean salad"
directions: Drain beans and combine in large bowl with dressing.
Add onion, if desired.
Chill, if you have time.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut bread into 4 squares.
Mix first 3 ingredients together. Spread onto bread; top with thin slice of cheese.
Broil until bubbly and serve.

title: mom's whirly-twirls(icebox cookie)
directions: Measure flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda; sift in a bowl.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and rum flavor.
Sift in dry ingredients gradually to make soft dough. Spoon 1/2 of dough into small bowl.
Blend in melted chocolate. Tint the other half with a few drops of red food color.
Roll out 1/2 dough of each color to a square between 2 sheets of wax paper. Peel off top sheets.
Lay red tinted dough paper side up on top of chocolate.
Peel off paper.
Roll up doughs, jelly roll fashion, using bottom paper as guide.
Wrap in clean wax paper.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Chill for 24 hours.
Unwrap dough right before baking.
Slice 1/8-inch thick with a sharp knife.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook milk, butter and sugar until soft ball forms.
Add peanut butter and stir.
Add oats; stir again.
Take a teaspoonful and drop onto a cookie sheet or foil.
Let cool.

title: peanut orange balls
directions: Combine peanuts, orange slices and coconut in a large mixing bowl.
Add milk, mixing well.
Shape in 1 inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Makes about 9 dozen.

title: quick cheese and bacon bread
directions: Add cream, eggs, bacon and milk. Stir all ingredients together with the Bisquick.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Spoon 3/4 full. You can sprinkle onion salt or garlic salt on top before baking or combine the two, if desired.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.
Serve with any meal.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done. Allow to cool. Cut lengthwise and scoop out soft center, keeping shell intact as much as possible.

title: coconut pecan filling and frosting
directions: Mix milk, sugar, margarine, egg yolks and vanilla in a large saucepan. Cook and stir on medium heat about 12 minutes or until thickened and golden brown. Remove from heat. Stir in coconut and pecans. Cool to room temperature and of spreading consistency. Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: creamy chicken manicotti(student favorite)
directions: Amounts should reflect tastes, appetites and number of people dining.

title: baked alaska(makes 4 servings)
directions: Cake should be 1 to 1 1/2-inches thick.
Cut cake into a rectangle that will be 1-inch wider and 1-inch longer than the ice cream brick.
Place cake on a small, thick wooden board.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Add sugar gradually and beat until mixture is thick, smooth, glossy and stands in firm peaks.
Place very hard brick of ice cream on cake and quickly spread meringue to completely and thickly cover the top and sides of ice cream and cake.
Place in a very hot oven (500°) and bake 3 to 4 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.
Remove from oven; immediately loosen from board and slide onto serving dish.
Slice and serve immediately while meringue is warm.

title: mexican scoop
directions: Blend dressing and sour cream.
Put in a pile in the center of a serving plate.
Top with 3 cheeses, all the vegetables and sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese on top.
Arrange nachos around the dip to use to scoop it up.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together eggs, oil and sugar.
Blend in flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Fold in apples and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for about one hour.
Wax paper line the pan or lightly grease and flour.
Makes a 13 x 9-inch oblong pan.
Enjoy!!!

title: very good biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in butter and add milk and cheese.
Mix as little as possible.
Drop by tablespoons on greased baking sheet with sides.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake for 12 minutes at 450°.
Serve warm.

title: spicy hot dogs or sausages
directions: Bring to a boil the chili sauce and pepper jelly.
Mix water and cornstarch; add to boiling mixture.
Stir until thickened. Add mini meats.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Beat until creamy. Pour in an 8 x 8-inch buttered pan. Cool and cut.

title: strawberry (chocolate) mousse dessert
directions: Mix, chill slightly, spread on top of cream cheese mix. Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.
For chocolate version, garnish with nuts and/or chocolate shavings.
Chill and enjoy!

title: old fashioned custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla. Slowly stir in hot milk.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle a little nutmeg over the top.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 425° and bake for 10 minute intervals until done.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook roast completely; slice into thin slices.
Saute onion; add other ingredients.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Layer meat and sauce in Dutch oven or big pan.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Serve on buns or rolls.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Divide ham into thirds.
Wrap an inch cube of cheese in ham. Tuck in pocket of chicken breasts.
Season.
Dip in melted butter, then in seasoned fine bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain grease.
Add enchilada sauce, milk and both cream soups.
Stir well until fully blended. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a pot and cover with water:
bring to a boil.
Cook until tender.
Drain potatoes and beat until they are light and fluffy.
Beat in butter and cream cheese, cut into small pieces.
Beat in sour cream and seasonings.
Put into a greased 9 x 13 inch casserole dish and refrigerate.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: mom's cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and chop bell pepper.
Mix cabbage and bell pepper together.
Salt cabbage and pepper.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Mix dressing (Miracle Whip, vinegar, sugar, pepper and milk). Pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pasta con piselli
directions: In large skillet fry bacon over medium heat until almost crisp.
Cut bacon into 2 inch pieces.
Add chopped onion to bacon and grease; cook until onion is tender.
Pour off about 1/3 of grease.
Mix in peas with juice.
Pour bacon mixture into large pot of cooked and drained ditalini.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with tossed garden salad and crispy garlic bread; outrageous!

title: grandma's easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in dish you plan to cook it in.
Add sugar, flour and milk.
Mix well.
Pour fruit in middle of dish.
Bake in a 350° oven until done, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, jello and flour and add Crisco, eggs and water.
Beat until blended and add strawberries.
Put into 3 cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 375°.

title: mom's best meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 12 ingredients; mix well. Press into an ungreased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drizzle top of loaf with ketchup.
Bake 15 minutes more or until no pink remains.
Makes 6 to 8 servings. Taken from "Taste of Home" magazine.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix.
Spoon into muffin tins.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix soups, rice and water.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Lay pieces of chicken on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 package of dry onion soup mix over chicken.
Seal tightly with foil and bake 2 hours at 325°.
"Do not peek."
Take foil off after 2 hours and leave in oven for 15 minutes with oven turned off.

title: boiled leg of boar with horseradish
directions: Place the leg of boar in a large pot.
Brown onions in a skillet in cooking oil and add these along with the garlic, a pinch of marjoram, parsley, wine, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer for 3 hours.
Serve with horseradish sauce.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Combine all but last 2 ingredients.
Put chocolate bits and nuts on the top, before you cook.
Put this in a pan (13 x 9-inch) and bake in oven at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: ham delights
directions: Split rolls (not individually but as a package).
Spread top and bottom with mixture of margarine, mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Add sliced ham and top ham with cheese slices.
Place parts of rolls together.
Wrap tightly in foil and heat 10 minutes at 400°.

title: batter bunnies(fritter fried rabbit)
directions: Cut rabbit in serving pieces.
Wash partially and cook in boiling water, simmering 20 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and onion according to taste.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix well first 3 ingredients with a spoon.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: chocolate covered crackers
directions: Cover cookie sheet with tinfoil.
Lay crackers salt side up (touching each other).
Boil brown sugar and butter.
Pour over crackers and bake in oven for 5 minutes on 400°.
Remove crackers from oven.
Pour chocolate chips evenly over crackers.
When chips melt, smooth to cover all cracker.
When totally cooled, break apart.

title: apple pecan cake
directions: Mix
together
Wesson oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour, cinnamon,
soda
and salt.
Add apple slices, pecans and coconut. Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken 'n mushrooms
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, poultry seasoning and sage. Slightly brown chicken in oil on both sides.
Mix together soup and mushrooms with any liquid.
Pour over chicken in skillet. Cover and simmer over low heat 15 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and milk in saucepan; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Pour in chocolate and stir until melted.
Add other ingredients; stir until blended.
Pour in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: simple meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pack into dish to bake.

title: sausage and bean filling(for mexican pizza)
directions: In a large frying pan, brown the sausage and onion until thoroughly cooked, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer one minute.
Spoon over crust.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes until filling is hot and bubbly.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Serve with crackers or Fritos and cheese.

title: curry chicken
directions: Place chicken in a casserole.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour, depends on the size of the pieces of chicken.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, margarine and nuts with pastry blender and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onions and pepper in a little water until soft.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut dates, nuts and candy in small pieces.
Add coconut and melted butter and pour over mixture.
Mix eggs, sugar, flour, soda and milk and pour over the other mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 2 hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Eggs should be beaten and margarine should be melted.
Add all ingredients together in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Chop bacon and onion; saute until nearly done.
Drain off about 1 cup liquid from beans and put beans into 5-quart casserole dish.
Add fried bacon, onion and drippings; stir.
Add 1 teaspoon pepper; stir.
Add 1/2 the sugar; stir.
Add pepper and garlic salt; stir.
Add rest of sugar and salt; stir.
Sprinkle rest of pepper over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, uncovered.

title: my favorite banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Gradually add sugar to shortening and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas, a small amount at a time, beating after each addition until smooth.
Turn into well-greased bread pan, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch and bake in a moderate oven at 350° about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: toffee turtle bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 1/2 cup margarine, brown sugar and flour until the texture is like fine crumbs.
Press firmly into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Set aside.

title: indian fried eggplant
directions: Wash eggplant.
Beat remaining ingredients with rotary beater until smooth.
Heat fat or oil (1 inch deep) to 375°F in large skillet.

title: diet muffins
directions: Cook at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vinegar and sugar.
Heat vinegar and sugar in a saucepan to boiling.
Pour over all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: harvard beets
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Add sugar and flour to saucepan.
Stir in vinegar and beet liquid until there are no lumps.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add beets; salt to taste.
Heat.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 2 minutes and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: no bake alaska
directions: Whip cream, using 2 teaspoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla, until it stands in peaks.
Place cake rounds on cookie sheet.
On each piece of cake, place 1 scoop ice cream.
Mound whipped cream over ice cream, covering completely.
Sprinkle crushed Whoppers over tops and sides of each mound.
Freeze until firm.
Serves 8.

title: jezebel sauce(ellie cummings)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
A wire whisk helps to mix them well.
Do this 3 days ahead of serving.
Mixture keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: gold fingers
directions: Combine ingredients to make thick batter.
Add 3 tablespoons vegetable mix and mix well.
Cut boned chicken breasts into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Dip in batter and deep fry at 350° for 3 minutes.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: fresh apple cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add vanilla and beat well. Sift together flour, baking powder and soda.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Add apples.
Blend thoroughly.
Place walnut-size bites of dough on greased cookie sheet and bake about 12 minutes in 350°.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Cook 1 chicken until tender.
Save broth.
Bone and cut into small pieces.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup broth and one can cream of chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Mix 1 cup self-rising flour, 1 stick margarine (melted), 1/2 teaspoon pepper and 1 cup buttermilk.
Spoon on top of chicken.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: baked haddock
directions: Put haddock in a Dutch oven on rack.
Salt and pepper fish. Slice the onion very thin and lay on fish.
In frying pan, brown cracker meal in butter (enough to cover fish).
Take shrimp soup and add 1 can milk; heat until warm.
Pour over fish.
Put in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes.
Do not cover; baste about twice.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix and let stand 24 hours before serving.

title: lemon pecan fruit cake
directions: Cream together brown sugar and butter; add eggs and flour; add cherries, pineapple, pecans and lemon extract.
Mix and bake for 2 or 3 hours at 300 degrees.
(I bake mine about 2 1/2 hours.) Don't overbake.

title: banana bread (2)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°F.

title: mango with cinnamon
directions: Chill mangos overnight.
To serve, place mango sections in dessert or fruit cup.
Top with coconut and sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Fry sausage and drain; cool.
Mix the rest into bowl.
When sausage is cool, mix together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple bars
directions: Combine the 2 cups flour, the 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt; cut in butter until crumbs are the size of peas.
Stir in egg yolks; divide mixture in half.
Press 1/2 over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine apples, remaining sugar, flour and cinnamon and arrange over dough.
Crumble remaining dough over apples; brush egg whites over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool; drizzle thin powdered sugar icing over top; cut in bars.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: christmas cranberry bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients and add the egg.
Combine the shortening and juice and grated rind of one orange and enough boiling water to total 3/4 cup of liquid.
Mix with the dry ingredients; add cranberries and nuts.
Bake for one hour at 325°. Slice the next day.

title: string pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cook beef and onion till brown; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.

title: 7 up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter, sugar, lemon flavor and eggs until creamy.
Add flour and 7-up.
Mix well, until all ingredients are blended.
Grease or spray tube pan, lightly flour. Pour batter into pan and bake for 1- 1/2 hours or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Open cans of crescent roll dough.
Cut through the indicated perforations to make eight dough triangles from each can.
Place a frankfurter in the center of each dough triangle.
Have children roll the dough around the frankfurter. The dough should be molded so that it completely surrounds the frankfurter.

title: kid size pizzas
directions: Roll or
pat
biscuits
into
to 2 1/2-inch circles. Place on
two
greased
cookie sheets.
In small bowl, combine tomato sauce, onion, garlic powder, oregano and basil;
spread over biscuits.
Sprinkle
with
cheese.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes
20 mini pizzas.
Toppings can vary according to your
child's favorite.
Also fun for kids to help make the pizzas.

title: eggnog trifle
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix, 2 tablespoons of juice and nutmeg.
Beat with wire whisk, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Slice cake horizontally into 4 layers.
Sprinkle cake layers evenly with remaining 2 tablespoons juice.
Cut in 1-inch cubes.
Place 2/3 of cake cubes in bottom of 2 1/2-quart straight sided bowl.
Spoon 2/3 of whipped topping over cake cubes.
Top with strawberries and toasted almonds.
Lay remaining cake cubes and whipped topping mixture over strawberries.
Garnish with reserved strawberries and almonds.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve. Makes 10 servings.

title: mushroom & asparagus stroganoff
directions: Coat large no-stick pan with no-stick spray.
Saute the red pepper, mushrooms, onions & asparagus over medium heat, about 5 minutes or until soft.

title: holiday fruit drops
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg well.
Stir in soured milk. Blend dry ingredients and add to previous mixture.
Add pecans, cherries and dates.
Chill at least one hour.

title: fruit 'n yogurt salad
directions: In small saucepan, combine pineapple liquid and mandarin orange liquid with cornstarch; mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cool slightly.
In large bowl, combine yogurt, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in cooled mixture.
Stir in pineapple, mandarin oranges, grapes, banana and apple slices.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Cover; refrigerate about 4 hours or until completely chilled.
Makes 12 servings.

title: italian sausage bread
directions: Butter the frozen loaf of bread.
Thaw loaf of bread dough, but don't let it rise (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Set aside.
Crumble and brown sausage in skillet; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients to browned sausage and mix well.
Roll out bread dough the length of a cookie sheet and about 6 inches wide.
Spread sausage mixture out evenly the length of the rolled out dough.
Roll up dough and sausage in pinwheel fashion, tucking under the ends.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Generously butter the top and sides of loaf. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Slice thinly when cooled.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat green beans to boiling.
In 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, spread green beans (drained).
Spread 1 can cream of celery soup over green beans.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread 1 can fried onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam cooking spray.
Layer frozen hash browns.
Heat together evaporated milk and margarine.
Pour over hash browns, just enough to cover.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and seasoning.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Let stand until room temperature.
Mix next two ingredients in separate bowl; stir. Set aside and stir later.
Add egg to yeast mixture.
In large bowl, mix flour and salt.
When all is melted and room temperature, add to flour and salt.
Stir with large fork until moist and elastic.
Pour in the buttered bowl.
Butter a large bowl and put back in it.
Cover with plastic wrap and put in refrigerator until cool.
Make rolls now or later.
Butter tops before letting rise in warm place until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: You will need 1 large Reynolds oven cooking bag (14 x 20-inch).

title: brownies
directions: Combine in order as listed.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until a toothpick placed in the center of pan comes out clean.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pudding and milk. Layer crackers and pudding in container. Spread frosting on top.

title: angie's cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
(If dry, add more Miracle Whip and pickle juice.)
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly and bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, green pepper, celery, mushrooms, onion, hard-boiled eggs and peas in glass serving dish.
Combine the mayonnaise, sugar, salt and garlic powder in bowl; mix well. Spread over peas.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Chill, covered, for 4 hours to overnight.

title: garlic romano vinaigrette
directions: Puree all ingredients in food processor.
Just before serving, drizzle dressing over platter of vegetables.

title: gazpacho(blender method)
directions: Put all ingredients into blender container.
Cover and process vegetables until coarsely chopped.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: honey mustard salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and refrigerate.

title: copper pennies
directions: Stir together remaining ingredients. Spoon over cooked carrots (drained).
Store in covered container.

title: pecan sandie dessert
directions: Combine crumbled cookies and oleo. Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and cool.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: In saucepan, saute onion in butter.
Add soups, Cheez Whiz and cooked rice.
Simmer.
Cook broccoli according to package directions, seasoning with butter and salt.
Drain.
Add broccoli to soup mixture.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Top with Progresso crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: blue fish cakes
directions: Cook fish in 1 cup vinegar, 6 cups water and 1/4 cup Old Bay. Drain.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels with evaporated milk. Mix cake mix with water, butter and eggs. Pour 1/2 batter in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Pour melted caramels over that. Sprinkle nuts and chips over caramels. Pour remaining batter over this and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Delicious.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place cut potatoes on cookie sheet (spray sheet with Pam).
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until tender and golden brown, stirring once.
Mix dressing, bacon, salt and pepper, onions and green pepper.
Add potatoes and mix well.
May serve hot or cold.

title: beef and tater casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef in 2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring once; drain.
Top with Tater Tots and minced onion.
Pour mixture of soups over top.
Microwave on High for 12 to 14 minutes or until heated through.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat spread and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Add dry ingredients with juice, mixing well after each addition. Stir in cranberries, nuts and peel.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk together.
Add powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Put a layer of graham crackers in bottom of large Pyrex dish.
Add half of the pudding mixture, another layer of graham crackers, the rest of the pudding mixture and last a layer of graham crackers.
Let chill to set to make spreading frosting easier.
After frosting, cover and keep refrigerated.

title: coconut cool whip cake
directions: Mix white cake as directions say on box.
Then bake in a 9 x 13 pan according to directions.
Poke holes in cake while hot and pour 1 can Eagle Brand milk and 1 small can Coco Lopez cream of coconut over cake.
Ice with 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Sprinkle flake coconut on top of Cool Whip.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream Crisco and butter.
Add sugar and cream until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool on wire racks for 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: In a large saucepan, combine gelatin with boiling water. Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts. Pour half the mixture into a 12 X 8 X 2 inch-baking dish. Refrigerate for 1 hr. or until firm. Spread with sour cream and spoon on the rest of gelatin mixture. Refrigerate. Cut into squares.

title: green chili appetizer
directions: Drain green chilies and spread on greased 10 x 10-inch casserole.
Over the chilies spread grated Cheddar cheese.
Mix eggs with milk and pour over the cheese.
Bake the casserole in a 350° oven about 25 minutes.
(It should be bubbly and slightly browned.)
Cut in pieces and serve on crackers.
This appetizer can be made ahead and frozen before baking.
If frozen, you will need to bake it longer.

title: gourmet "steaks"
directions: Shape ground beef into 6 large oval patties.
Grill or broil until desired doneness.
Combine mushroom gravy, soy sauce and almonds.
Heat and serve over patties.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco filling
directions: Brown pork with onion.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
When browned well, mix in flour.
Add a little warm water, the can of tomato sauce and banana pepper.
Simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Serve on warmed taco or burrito shell.
Garnish with chopped tomatoes, lettuce, additional hot sauce (if needed) and shredded cheese.

title: shirley's jellied lime salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk over double boiler.
Pour mixture over jello and stir until dissolved.
Stir in cream cheese until well blended.
Add undrained pineapple.
Let cool.
Blend in whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Turn into greased 2-quart ring mold and chill until firm.
Serves approximately 12.
Can be made day before.
Can add nuts for variety.

title: grandma's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, brown sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix all these ingredients well.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
These ingredients can all be mixed in an electric mixer or by hand.
Drop teaspoonful of batter into a tray of confectioners sugar.
Roll batter until covered with sugar and put onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
For an added taste, add 1/2 cup coconut to batter. Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: In large bowl, pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Vigorously beat in the remaining ingredients.
Fill greased muffin pans 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Makes about 30 medium to large size muffins.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix sugar and butter, then stir in nuts, raisins, cocoa, coconut and rum. Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour. Shape into 3/4-inch balls and roll in coconut. Chill on waxed paper-lined tray. Makes about 30.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on cookies.

title: apple oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder, spices and salt; add to egg mixture.
Stir in oats and apples; beat well.
Fold in nuts and raisins (optional).
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry-apple cooler
directions: In large saucepan combine 1/2 of cranberry juice, all of cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to boil.
Simmer, covered for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Discard cinnamon and cloves.
Add remaining cranberry juice.
Add apple juice and water.
Pour all in 2-quart pitcher.
Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: deep dish sausage pizza
directions: Brown sausage and onion in 12-inch skillet with ovenproof handle.
Drain fat.
Remove sausage and onion from skillet; set aside.

title: jello mold
directions: Drain pineapple juice and add 1/2 cup of water to jello.
Boil water on stove.
Put jello in bowl and put into refrigerator until it jells.
(Don't let it get hard.)

title: mushroom soup
directions: Wash and peel 1 quart mushrooms; cut into dice.
Stir into them 1 1/2 quarts of good rich stock, veal or chicken.
Thicken with 1 tablespoon flour creamed with 1 tablespoon butter and 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon of pepper.
At last moment, add a bit of whipped cream and croutons.

title: pot roast of beef
directions: Put vegetables in bottom of crock-pot, salt and pepper meat to taste and put in pot.
Add liquid.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours; on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Remove meat and vegetables with spatula and thicken for gravy, if desired.

title: i have to have dessert now!
directions: Place ice cream sandwiches in bottom of pan.
Cover with Cool Whip and cherries (sparingly).
Freeze.
Slice when ready to serve.

title: cream of corn soup
directions: Melt butter and simmer onion until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add corn, half and half and cream.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes being careful not to boil.

title: easy chicken & rice casserole
directions: Butter large casserole or 9x13-inch pan.
Put rice on bottom of pan.
Place chicken pieces on rice.
Dilute chicken soup with 1 can of water and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with oregano, parsley flakes, garlic salt (no powder) and pepper.
Dust with paprika.
Cover with foil and bake 2-3 hours at 300 to 325° or 1 to 1/2 hours at 350°.
Bake last 10-15 minutes without foil covering.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix muffin mix as directed and add creamed corn.
Brown hamburg; drain grease and add taco sauce and simmer 10 minutes. Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 muffin mix into pan.
Spread with meat; add cheese.
Pour remaining muffin mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy pot roast
directions: A crock-pot is needed.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together and pour into a hot skillet with bacon grease. Bake at 375° about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Press croissants into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Put cheese layer, ham layer and more cheese.
Pour milk and egg mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas in cream
directions: Combine chicken, salsa and green chilies.
Fill each tortilla with a portion of the chicken mixture.
Roll up and place seam side down in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour cream over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden and most of the cream is absorbed.
Makes 6 servings.
Can be made ahead of time putting cream and grated cheese on just before cooking.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Precook the first 4 ingredients until tender.
Add chicken and peas and pour into large casserole dish.
Mix soup and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Combine flour, milk and the melted margarine.
Stir well until most lumps are gone.
Pour over the chicken and vegetable mixture.
Do not stir.
Cook at 400° until brown and bubbly.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Do not salt chicken.

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and put into refrigerator.

title: frozen strawberry pie
directions: READ COMPLETE INSTRUCTIONS BEFORE STARTING.
BE SURE PECANS ARE FREE OF HULLS AND TRASH.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place warm water in bowl.
Add dry milk and mix well.
Add sugar and mix until smooth.
You may find it helpful in dissolving sugar to set the bowl in a pan of hot water.

title: green tomato pickle relish
directions: Slice tomatoes and onions.
Chop up peppers.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight; drain.
Boil the sugar and seasonings with vinegar approximately 5 minutes.
(Tie spices in a bag.)
Cool slightly.
Add tomatoes, etc., and simmer approximately 60 minutes until a syrup forms.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Pout into glass serving bowl. Chill.

title: crusty (soft center) spoon bread
directions: Combine, then sift, the corn meal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add 1 beaten egg and 1 cup of milk; blend well. Melt oleo in baking dish.
Pour in batter.
Pour 1/2 cup of milk over top of mixture, but do not stir.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease oblong Pyrex baking dish.
Layer broccoli, then chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and spoon and spread on top.
Add rice if you are using it with the chicken. Saute bread crumbs in butter.
Sprinkle on the cheese.
Top with bread crumbs last.
Can garnish with pimento strips.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Prepare 1 chicken breast for each person.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar and flour in top of double boiler; stir in egg yolks and milk and blend well.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Cover bottom of casserole with layers of vanilla wafers, alternating with layers of bananas.
Pour custard over; continue to layer wafers and bananas and end with custard.
Beat egg whites until stiff; spread on top of pudding.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Chop or shred cabbage; sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours.
Squeeze liquid out.
Mix cabbage, celery and pepper.
Mix vinegar, water, sugar, celery and mustard seed in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Place in small containers and freeze.
Thaw in refrigerator and serve very cold.

title: blueberry cheesecake dessert
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, water and berries and cook over low heat until thick.
Let cool.
Combine cracker crumbs and butter; set aside.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in pan as follows: 3/4 crumb mixture, 1/2 cream cheese, berry mixture and 1/2 cream cheese.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Cool thoroughly before serving.

title: cornbread cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; blend nuts last.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ground meat soup
directions: In a small amount of oil (canola), cook meat, but not brown. Add next 3 ingredients. Saute 2 to 3 minutes, just to wilt. Add onion soup and 1 quart water. Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Add mixed vegetables and 1 quart water. Bring to a boil. Add pasta. Cook 10 to 15 minutes. Add tomatoes and corn.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Adjust seasoning. Add water, if thinner soup is preferred.

title: italian shells casserole
directions: Cook shells until al dente.
Rinse and drain.
Brown ground chuck.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in marinara sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Line bottom of lasagna pan with half of shells.
Spread half of sour cream over shells.
Sprinkle half of each cheese over this.
Repeat second layer.
Cover pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put the sugar and cinnamon in a bag or container. Quarter biscuits.
Shake a few of the biscuit quarters at a time in the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Then place all in a lightly greased Bundt pan.
Melt 1/2 stick of margarine, 3/8 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Drizzle this over biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: leonard blush fruit slush
directions: In a large container, combine the warm water and sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Add the mashed bananas and the juice. Freeze mixture.
Remove mixture from the freezer 30 minutes before serving.
Scoop into glasses and pour 7-Up or ginger ale over frozen mixture.
Makes about 26 servings.

title: mrs. jessie's vinegar pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add to creamed butter.
Add beaten eggs, vinegar and water.
Pour into 2 uncooked pie shells and cook 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Cook hamburger meat and drain.
Add other ingredients except cheese.
Put other ingredients in crock-pot, then cut cheese in cubes.
Melt cheese and stir together until cheese is melted.
It is ready to serve.
Serve with tortilla chips or Doritos chips.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Melt butter, add onions and garlic.
Saute until wilted.
Add spinach and artichokes.
Cook about 3-5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well. Heat to melt cheese in microwave or on low heat.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Sour cream and salsa optional.

title: cough syrup(home remedy)
directions: Take 1/2 to 1 teaspoon every few hours.
Our family doctor prescribed this for us.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt to hard ball stage (250°), then add Marshmallow Creme to bowl.
Stir in hot syrup, leaving until soft, then drop in spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients, but chocolate.
Melt chocolate and pour over mixture.
Mix well and spread on wax paper.
Let stand until hard.
Break apart.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Combine fruit with 1/2 cup flour mixture.
Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Combine soda and buttermilk.
Add to combined mixture with remaining flour mixture. Blend well after each addition.
Stir in candy; mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: crescent yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water or milk.
Beat eggs and add sugar, then melted margarine and salt.
Combine with yeast and water or milk.
Add flour, mixing until well blended.
(The dough will be soft.)
Place in refrigerator until doubled in size or overnight.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix up cake as directed on cake mix box. In separate bowl, mix pudding with milk.
Fold pudding mixture into cake mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes.
While still hot from oven, put unwrapped Hershey bars on top.
Let melt and spread.

title: date loaf cake
directions: Mix and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Use a 10-inch tube pan.

title: canned green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except beans in pot.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Then put in beans.
When they begin to boil, count 40 minutes boiling time.
Put in jars and seal.
Store in cool place.

title: apricot salad
directions: Put jello, sugar, crushed pineapple in pan and bring to a boil.
Then cool.
After it is cool, add Cool Whip and buttermilk. Put in refrigerator to set.
Can be put in a loaf pan and sliced on lettuce leaves.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Dip any raw vegetable in this.
Delicious.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Add powdered sugar, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Next, add the dry ingredients.
Shape into rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill for at least 3 hours.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Mix butter, sugar, cinnamon and flour in small bowl and let stand.
Wash apples and pare apples.
Cut in about 1/2 inch slices. Add water.
Arrange apples in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle apples with sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: microwave fries
directions: Place a sheet of Reynolds microwave wrap on a microwave safe plate, set aside.
In a medium bowl, mix garlic salt, paprika, pepper and oil.
Cut each potato quarter into 4 or 5 thin wedges. Toss potato wedges in spice mixture until evenly coated.
Arrange potato wedges, cut side down, on microwave cooking paper. Sprinkle potato wedges with parmesan cheese.
Microwave at high for 5 to 7 minutes or until potatoes are tender, rotating dish once.
Let stand 1 minute.
Serve immediately.

title: french onion soup
directions: Separate onions into rings and cook in 2 tablespoons butter/margarine just until glossy.
Add consomme, water, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Spread remaining butter on one side of each piece of French bread.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place bread under broiler until brown.
Put one piece of bread on each bowl of soup.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add well beaten eggs.
Mix all other ingredients.
Cook in loaf pan for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: brown bean chowder
directions: Cook beans in 3 quarts water or more if needed.
When beans are nearly done, add 2 tablespoons chili powder and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
While beans are cooking, combine meat, onions and garlic; brown in skillet on top of stove or brown in 350° oven, stirring frequently until done.
Add puree, 1 tablespoon chili powder, 1 tablespoon salt and bread crumbs; simmer 15 minutes. Combine meat mixture and beans.
May have to add more water for desired thickness or more chili powder for desired season.
Yields 12 servings, approximately 3 quarts.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: apple dabble cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: tomato juice
directions: Run tomatoes through sieve to remove seeds and skin.
Add other ingredients; bring to boiling, then put in jars.
Cold pack for 10 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: pecan honeymoon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend shortening and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add 1 cup flour and salt.
Stir in milk.
Pat evenly in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes or until light brown.
Beat eggs; add 1 cup brown sugar and vanilla. Beat until thick.
Stir remaining ingredients.
Pour onto mixture in pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown. Cool.
Frost and garnish with cherries, if desired.
Cut into squares.

title: high peaks stew
directions: Brown the meat; drain.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cook until almost tender.
Add rest of vegetables.
Cook until carrots are tender.

title: hickory fish bake
directions: Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
Arrange half the lemon slices in bottom of a shallow baking pan.
Add fish in single layer.
Place remaining lemon on top.
Combine butter and garlic. Pour over top of fish.
Add hickory to slow coals, place baking pan atop grill.
Close hood and cook 25 to 30 minutes, basting frequently.
Serve with lemon slices and butter mixture.

title: chicken party shells
directions: Chop chicken into cubes.
Thaw party shells.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven until lightly brown.
Mix all ingredients and fill shells.
Sprinkle more cheese on each shell. Return to oven and heat until cheese melts.

title: russian tea(makes 4 cups of mix)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in airtight container. Use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water or 3 teaspoons per mug.

title: stuffed clams
directions: Mix clam sauce with bread crumbs so mixture holds together but is not too dry.
Spoon into cleaned, empty clam shells.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until set.
Yields approximately 20 appetizers.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift in flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add grated carrots and nuts.
Carrots may be grated in blender.
Pour in floured, ungreased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done; cool.
May be frozen.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: breaded pineapple
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in casserole dish; put bread crumbs on top and pour melted oleo over them.
Bake 45 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.
Great side dish for pork or ham.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix ingredients and press into bottom of large baking dish. Bake 15 minutes at 350° and let cool.

title: peanut butter sighs
directions: Microwave peanut butter and margarine on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until margarine melts.
Stir in xxx sugar.
Spread mixture in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Soften chocolate on Medium-High 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir to remove lumps.
Do not overcook.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Sprinkle with xxx sugar.
Refrigerate.
Cut or break into pieces.

title: cheddar blocks
directions: Mix and bake 25 to 30 minutes in greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Slice into small blocks for finger food.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: Dissolve 1 yeast cake in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add boiling water to shredded wheat biscuits.
Let cook down, add yeast mixture.
Add rest of ingredients.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl and grease surface of dough lightly. Cover.
Let rise until double.
Knead and divide in half.
Shape into loaves.
Put in 2 loaf pans.
Cover and let rise.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and continue baking 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bill's easy apple butter
directions: In a large kettle, to measured applesauce, add the exact amount of sugar specified.
Stir in lemon juice and spices. Bring to a full rolling boil and boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in Certo at once.
Stir to cool slightly.
Pour into jelly glasses or odds and ends of small jars. Cover with a thin layer of paraffin wax.
After it cools some, put lids on.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Mix all together in crock-pot.
Top with cheese.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: ugly face cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and Bisquick.
Add eggs and oil.
Beat by hand until most of the lumps have disappeared.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar until well mixed.
Add extract and eggs and mix thoroughly.
Stir in flour mixture.
Mix well. This will make a soft, sticky dough.
Place in a tight container or roll in foil and season overnight in the refrigerator.

title: snacking dip for chips
directions: Drain tuna; combine all ingredients.
Arrange potato chips, celery sticks or tomatoes on platter.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Blend flour and softened margarine.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle and pat into flour mixture almonds and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Blend cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Put on top of crust.
Mix pudding and milk and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with more almonds, mini chocolate chips, etc.
Keep refrigerated until served.
Makes approximately 15 servings.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine egg, cracker crumbs, onion, 1/3 cup tomato sauce, oregano, salt and pepper; mix well and add to meat.
Mix thoroughly; shape into flat rectangle, about 10 x 12 inches, on waxed paper.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over meat.
Roll up like a jelly roll; press ends of roll to seal.
Place on rack in shallow baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour.
Drain off excess fat. Pour on remaining tomato sauce; bake an additional 15 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Add as many pecans and small marshmallows as you like.
You can also add sliced bananas.
Mix all together and chill before serving.
This makes quite a bit and is very easy.

title: smoked sausage red beans and rice
directions: Add all ingredients except rice into a large pot.
Cook on medium heat 1 1/2 hours.
Prepare rice.
Serve beans and sausage over rice.

title: butterscotch	brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine first 3 ingredients. Melt morsels over heat (not boiling) water.
Transfer to bowl. Add brown sugar. Cool 5 minutes.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Blend in flour mixture. Stir in nuts. Spread in greased 15 x 10 pan. Bake 30 minutes.

title: cheese vegetable soup
directions: Dump both cans of soup into large pot.
Whisk soup as you add water.
Add vegetable of choice.
Cook until partially tender. Add Velveeta, stirring constantly until melted, over medium heat. If you don't, the cheese will scorch bottom of the pot and will possibly boil over.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Chop the rhubarb into 1/4-inch pieces; sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and set aside.
Cream the shortening, salt, 1 3/4 cups brown or white sugar and vanilla.
Add the eggs.
Add alternately the buttermilk, soda, flour and cinnamon.
Mix in rhubarb.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add topping.

title: saucy green beans
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Blend in flour, salt, sugar and milk.
Cook until smooth.
Add vinegar and sour cream; pour over beans.
Place over low heat to heat to serving temperature.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs.
Beat well, then add peanut butter.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to first mixture, then fold in water and vanilla.
Shape dough into teaspoon-size balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press flat with a fork dipped in cold water.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan and sprinkle the nuts in the bottom.
Place rolls upright in grooves of pan.
Sprinkle pudding and cinnamon mix over top.
Pour melted margarine and sugar over the top.
Cover with towel and let set overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Beat eggs with 1/4 teaspoon salt and fry in 2 tablespoons hot oil.
Cook until dry and separated.
Remove eggs.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil.
Add green onions, then rice.
Stir-fry 5 minutes and then add chicken broth and soy sauce.
Add eggs and chicken strips (pre-fried).
Heat together, stirring occasionally, on medium heat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Cover with water.
Add lemon juice and cook about 10 minutes.
Remove potatoes from water.
Mix potato water and other ingredients; bring to a boil.
Alternate potatoes and pastry in casserole dish.
Pour boiling mixture over potatoes. Add top crust and brush with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: friendship cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass jar with a loose cover. Stir several times the first day, then stir once a day.
At the end of 2 weeks the Starter has fermented to make sauce.

title: chili(quick, easy and good)
directions: In large skillet brown ground beef, drain off fat.
Add chili seasoning mix.
In 6-quart kettle heat tomato paste, beans and water, stirring continuously.
Add ground beef to bean mixture and cook together for a few minutes.

title: chicken delight
directions: Boil chicken, green pepper, onion and tomatoes until done. Add rice and let simmer. Add cooked spaghetti and serve.

title: ginger lime dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and chill. Serve with fruit.
Makes 1 cup.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Bake brownies according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Prepare mousse according to directions, but do not chill.
In 3-quart trifle dish, layer half the brownie pieces, half the mousse, half the candy and half the Cool Whip.
Repeat the layers.
Garnish with chocolate curls. Chill 8 hours.

title: creamy chicken bake
directions: Place chicken breasts in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and milk and spread over cheese.
Toss melted butter with stuffing mix and sprinkle over top of chicken. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Put sliced potatoes in baking dish.
Add 1 1/2 cups water.
Add sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cut 1/2 stick butter on this. Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Put 1 stick butter on top.
Bake at 250° to 275° until brown.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350°.

title: mexican roll-up
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread on flour tortilla. Chill.
Cut in slices 1-inch thick.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Cook noodles and add to hamburger, mushrooms and sauces.
Pour half of mixture into a 12 1/4 x 10 1/4 x 2 1/4-inch casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 of cheese, then add rest of mixture and top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: When slightly thickened, spoon over cheese layer and chill.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut lard with pastry blender.
Combine with other ingredients. Mix 1 egg and 1 tablespoon vinegar in 1 cup measure.
Fill to 1 cup level with cold water.
Mix into dry ingredients.
Knead only until smooth.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Put sweet potatoes in baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt.
Put applesauce on top.
Mix brown sugar, rolled oats and cinnamon together.
Stir in butter.
Sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 370° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Cut
up
okra,	tomatoes,
green
peppers,
onions
and celery.
Put a little bacon grease in skillet.
Lump it all in and season with Lawry's seasoned salt and black pepper.
Add a little water as it cooks.

title: sesame strips
directions: Cut crust from white bread.
Brush on both sides with melted butter.
(Chop garlic clove in butter while melting or add garlic powder.)
Cut each slice into 4 strips and dip both sides in mixture of Parmesan cheese and sesame seed.
Bake 45 minutes at 250° or 10 minutes at 350°, then 20 minutes at 250°.
Keep in tins. Run in oven to "crisp-up".

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in warm water; add sugar, salt and oil. Add flour until dough thickens.
Add flour so dough is soft, but not sticky.
Let rise to double.
Pan out onto 2 cookie sheets. Top with pizza sauce and your favorite toppings.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until bottom is brown.
Then top with Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven and bake about 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Bake the chocolate cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to the directions on box.
Let cool, then break into bite-size chunks and place in a large Tupperware bowl with lid.
Pour 1 cup Kahlua over cake; mix around to soak in flavor.
Let marinate in refrigerator overnight until next day.
In glass bowl, layer 1/2 of the cake mix, 1/2 of the Cool Whip, then 1/2 of the Heath bar pieces.
Repeat.
Add chocolate shavings, if desired.
Tastes as good as it looks.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 350°.
Cool before cutting.

title: dirty rice
directions: Simmer livers, peppers, onions and celery in oil with 2 cups water until tender and water is cooked out. Add 1/8 teaspoon red pepper, salt and black pepper to taste.
Place in blender and blend well. Add to cooked rice.
Reheat and serve. Double this for large crowds. Also this freezes well.

title: chili bake(goes with cornbread topping.)
directions: Melt shortening in
large
skillet.
Add
onion,
green pepper and beef; brown
lightly.
Drain off 1/2 cup juice from can of tomatoes.
To
mixture
in skillet add tomatoes, kidney beans, salt, chili
powder
and
pepper.
Mix
all ingredients well. Pour into a 2 quart casserole dish.
Top with Cornbread Topping and bake.

title: fudge cupcakes
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into muffin pans, lined with cupcake fillers and bake at 350° until springy, about 18 minutes.
Cover with chocolate frosting.
Makes 3 dozen.
Very moist.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix food coloring and cocoa and set aside.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and coloring.
Beat 10 minutes. Add buttermilk.
Slowly add flour then salt and vanilla.
Mix vinegar and soda.
Add to batter mixing lightly by hand.
Pour into two 9-inch greased and floured cake pans or a 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together ingredients and put in refrigerator for several hours before serving.
This can be made the night before.
Just before serving, chop up 2 bananas and mix with other ingredients.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix together and put in pan.
Press chicken down in mixture and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Cover with foil.
Some water may need to be added to keep from getting dry.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal and next 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine broccoli and next 5 ingredients.
Stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened.
Place a 9-inch cast-iron skillet in a 425° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; heavily coat with cooking spray. Immediately spoon batter into skillet and bake at 425° for 28 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: spinach tortilla pinwheel sandwiches
directions: Mix together well and spread on 10 large flour tortillas. Roll up and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight and cut into pinwheels.

title: parmesan salad
directions: Break broccoli flowerets into bite size pieces.
Thinly slice stem portion.
Combine with cauliflower, onion and 3/4 jar of bacon pieces.
Toss with combined mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle with remaining bacon pieces.
Serves 6.

title: lollipop recipe
directions: In a saucepan, blend sugar, corn syrup and water.
Bring to boil over high heat until mixture reaches 290°.
Remove pan from heat.
Allow to stand until bubbles have simmered down.
Add flavoring and color as desired.
Do not overstir.
Mold into desired shapes in Pam sprayed hard candy molds.
Work fast!

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
(Can take skin off first; optional.) Brown chicken in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover pan.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box and let cool.
Break one layer into pieces in punch bowl.
Cover with half of pudding, then layer half of bananas, 1 can of pineapple, 1 can cherry pie filling and half of coconut.

title: doves in madeira sauce
directions: Rub doves inside and out with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Brown in 3 tablespoons butter in a casserole dish, then saute the onions in 2 tablespoons butter.

title: onion casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious!

title: pastel cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking powder.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and Jell-O, beating well.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Force dough through cookie press onto ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with additional Jell-O (same flavor).
Bake about 8 minutes at 400° or until edges are brown.
Makes about 10 dozen 1 to 1 1/2-inch cookies.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix 2 cups of sugar with apple cubes and let stand for 1 hour. Blend the oil and eggs with apple mixture.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to apple mixture.
Stir just until blended. Add nuts and raisins.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese into large bowl and let stand at room temperature until softened.
Add oleo.
Mix salt, pepper and flour.
Gradually work into cheese-butter mixture.
Blend until smooth.
Using a cookie press, squeeze out cheese straws onto ungreased baking sheets.
Cut into 2 to 3-inch lengths.
Bake for about 15 minutes until crisp and golden.
Do not allow to brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in carrots and orange juice.
Stir in flour mixture with spoon.
Stir in orange rind, raisins and walnuts. Spread batter in 2 (8-inch) round cake pans, greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper in oil.
Add remaining ingredients (except spaghetti) and heat well.
Cook spaghetti and add to sauce.
Put in baking dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Add extra cheese on top before baking, if desired.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and applesauce. Sift together dry ingredients; add to the mixture alternately with water.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef, garlic, salt and chopped onion.
Drain oil. Add 1/2 pound grated cheeses; heat until melted.
Add sour cream, sliced mushrooms and olives; set aside.
Soften 12 corn tortillas in hot oil; drain.
Fill each tortilla with meat mixture; roll tightly.
Place seam side down on foil-lined cookie sheet (spray foil with cooking spray so cheese won't stick).
Top with slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Cover with foil (sprayed).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: strawberry or raspberry delight
directions: Thoroughly mix in order first 5 ingredients.
Chill to egg white consistency.
Whip whipping cream.
Fold into chilled jello mixture.
Tear up angel food cake.
Place layer of cake bits in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon jello and cream over cake.
Repeat with layer of cake, layer of mixture until used up.
Chill several hours.
Makes 24 small servings.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash and sterilize jars.
Put onion slice in bottom of jars. Mix all ingredients to make a cold syrup.
